a987eda3-95cd-49fc-b4dd-3d455582c745	cmp239xby000cml2ua4byus1o	I don’t have many photos, but I had to leave a review because their professional handling of our 31-person group was top-tier. From the booking process to room assignments and luggage logistics, everything was smooth as silk.\n\nWhen we arrived, every room was already sorted exactly as requested, singles, doubles, kings, all assigned to the right names with receipts and paperwork ready for signature. No mess, no waiting. Even better, when we returned from an excursion from Machu Picchu, all our luggage was already organized in the lobby exactly as instructed, ready to go. For a group this size, that’s five-star service.\n\nThe rooms were quiet, and the hot water was excellent (a must!). The location is a bit away from the center, but we knew that beforehand, plus, a Tuk-Tuk only costs 5 Sol and they’re easy to find. The courtyard with alpacas is a great touch, and the staff were genuinely friendly.\n\nThe breakfast spread was huge. My only tiny suggestion? I’d love to see some sugar-free yogurt options next time. Other than that, the stay was flawless. Highly recommended!	Pazu P	5
