4e7e6b08-f6ea-4b9d-8b8b-6ae75414ab5e	cmp1t7ezl009sml2iympo3ci6	I just completed a 3 week stay here with Sergey, it was an unbelievable experience. Met some great people here enjoyed our conversations around the fire. Amazing what just a week or 2 can do for you! I first had planned to stay 2 weeks but after the first ceremony I realised that I would need to extend another week. I knew this was a very special medicine from the first time I tried it the year before and knew I had to return to it.\nThe healing and processing I experienced here was remarkable, the pace and relaxed atmosphere Sergey created here at Huachuma Wasi really allows you the time and space to explore yourself and your life, it helped me so much in coming to terms with many things but also allowed me to look forwards towards a brighter future and gain clarity on how I want to live and show up.\nSergey is a wonderful guide, who has a positive and infectious attitude and has just the words, at times our conversations became my medicine…shifting the experience as he knew just what to say and when to say it.\nI appreciate you and your family for providing such a welcoming and healing environment. I will be back for sure, and look forward to seeing where my next steps take me. Thanks again Sergey!	Isaac Whittaker	5
604a5606-9f5f-4d60-aff6-8eb3fe8d94b7	cmp1t7ezl009sml2iympo3ci6	Huachuma Wasi is a magical place, filled with deep wisdom and beautiful energy. Even simply being in the garden brings me a deep sense of peace and joy.\n\nI first came a year ago with my partner and knew I would return. I came back again this year, and it has had a deeply positive impact on our relationship, there is something truly special about sharing this experience together.\n\nThe longer I stay, the deeper I go, and each time it becomes more powerful and heart opening. I left this time with real clarity on the path I’m meant to walk, shedding confusion, fears, and doubts.\n\nWe were welcomed with genuine warmth by Sergey and his family, creating a space where I felt safe and at home. Over time, a deep sense of trust naturally builds with Sergey, which makes it possible to fully surrender to the process. I’m truly grateful to be here and to drink his medicine. Sergey’s guidance plays a major role, he is clear, practical, and reassuring, helping me truly understand and integrate the experience.\n\nI felt real bliss, and connected deeply with the medicine, nature, the land, its ancestors, and most importantly my true self.\nHuachuma shows you the truth and guides you, but it is up to you to make the choice—to have the will to change and to walk the right path.\n\nThe people I met became lifelong friends. I connected with them on a soul level, and even if we don’t stay in touch often, I know the love remains and is always felt.\n\nFor me, this is a life changing experience that shifts my perception of fundamental truths. Huachuma Wasi is a place I will always return to, to go deeper, rebalance, live from the heart, and align my mind.\n\nI want to give a special thanks to Sergey for the trust he creates, the friendship, his humor, his practicality, and above all his support.\n\nI now walk my path with love by listening to my heart, with loyalty to myself and the people I love, and with great courage.\n\nHasta luego 🌵🫶🏻💫	Jihane Berbery	5
061ec2ba-9b6c-4616-853d-33ddc36ed470	cmp1t7ezl009sml2iympo3ci6	So grateful that I had the chance to stay at Huachuma Wasi and experience the medicine. Although I have stayed only one week I truly got more than I expected. Sergey is an amazing human being and his guidance make this experience even more life changing. He is very supportive along the process and guides you with love, trust and safety. After many years I found the clarity I have been seeking through love, empathy and self respect. Also sharing your experience by the fire with the group was a healing process on its own and I am really grateful for the people I have met and the stories we shared. I will remember all of you forever! Thank you Huachuma and Sergey for everything, this is not a goodbye. See you soon!	Dimitris Zisis	5
88ba6b29-1a2d-409f-891e-54fba758de7f	cmp1t7ezl009sml2iympo3ci6	Huachuma Wasi, what a beautiful place! From the moment you step in through the door to the garden you feel peace. Sergey makes the place feel like home and the ceremonies super safe. With his guidance he makes sure we find the healing and the serenity we are looking for. As someone that has no past experience with medicinal plants, I can guarantee that thanks to Sergey there is nothing to be afraid of.\nAfter every ceremony we share our experience of the day by the fire, and this sharing alone is powerful.\nApart from the huachuma ceremonies, Sergey is always available to help you plan your visits to any other place you would like to explore around Sacred Valley. Great host!\nOverall, amazing energy!! Thanks Sergey and your family for these unforgettable moments we shared.	Konstantina Mameletzi	5
561af048-29f5-4cf2-9c4b-60bdefebe1b0	cmp1t7ezl009sml2iympo3ci6	My stay az Huachuma Wasi was perfectly what I needed right now.  I didn't plan to come but I had dreams, signs and a strong calling so I changed my plans to fit it in. I arrived and settled in, got the most beautiful room on top of the house,  with windows to all 4 directions with view to the mountains. We had some introductory talk, also talked about my previous experiences, then we had a bit of free time to look around in the town of Calca with other participants. Everyone was so kind and openminded, but at the same time grounded which made me feel safe and comfortable with them from the first day.\nSergey takes special care of everyone. He made sure we had everything, reminded us to prepare our tea, warm and waterproof clothes for the ceremony days. He introduced us into the medicine gradually, first with a small amount checking our sensitivity, then based on our experiences we might "leveled up". I felt completely safe and I could entirely trust the medicine and his expertise after the first day so I chose to level up.\nThe first day was also really wonderful, I wrote a lot, aligned my thoughts about my life, my values, commited to new goals. There was also a lot of healing that just happened at times when I let go of thinking and just allowed myself to recieve. We all had our own place we chose for ourselves so that we could pay attention to our own process and connect with the beautiful nature around. Sergey came by to check on us several times and was available to talk about anything that came up. I really appreciate his wisdom, listening to him I learnt and healed a lot even things I didn't know I was still carrying. I'm also really glad that I went for more at my second ceremony because this way I got to experience the whole thing much more deeply. I wrote less, but experienced every moment. I allowed myself to become the person I truely want to be from my heart, I found the deepest meaning of love, respect, care, oneness, connection to nature, spirit and God by really experiencing everything fully. I sang a lot, mostly to express my love and gratitude. Just into the universe, to the unseen. Also for myself to have some recordings of the new me, brave and strong, living from the heart. I sang also to Sergey, to express my everlasting deep gratitude for guiding me here and throughout the whole process, supporting when needed, for the messages he transmitted, and for whole setup of the retreat itself.\nThe integration around the fire and dinner together was also so special, we all shared openly and honestly, I thank also this small community that formed during my stay.\nSo what I can share is that for me this plant is a magical medicine to come back to my center, to understand and feel my whole being, human and spiritual experience much better and I am really grateful for the medicine too!\nMaybe it's colors, sensations, thoughts, feelings, understanding or deep healing how the medicine works with you but from my experience this is a beautiful upgrade and a new beginning, a strong and confident push towards your best life.🙏🏻	Borbála Szondy	5
