8199f15d-5646-44e3-992d-7b32f4eda97e	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	Mi experiencia con Explorandes en mi viaje ha Cusco, Valle Sagrado y Machupichu ha sido inolvidable. Todo el equipo se mostró siempre profesional, amable y disponible las 24 horas, anticipándose a mis necesidades y cuidando cada detalle del viaje.\n\nQuiero destacar especialmente a sus guías, personas con gran conocimiento de la historia, la cultura y las tradiciones locales, que lograron transmitir su pasión por el Perú de una manera cercana y auténtica.\n\nLas rutas elegidas, los hoteles recomendados y las sugerencias gastronómicas superaron mis expectativas. Más que una agencia de viajes, Explorandes ha sido un verdadero compañero de viaje, combinando organización impecable con un trato muy cercano y humano.	Almudena Gurpegui Sedano	5
91c41ebd-7e2e-49ac-9fe4-eb3fd5ba1cba	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	I am so grateful for Explorandes and our guide, Pamela. This was truly a once-in-a-lifetime experience and the company couldn't have made it any more perfect. Yes, the views were absolutely breathtaking, but my favorite part of this trip was Pamela. She is one of the most thoughtful, caring, and knowledgable people I have ever met. It's clear how much she loves her job, and it shines through everything she does. Even after the trip ended, my group and I couldn't stop talking about how wonderful Pamela was.\n\nMake sure to book Explorandes (and Pamela) if you're planning a Machu Picchu trip!!	Taylor Berberich	5
cff93b19-336f-43c2-9ec2-d5246c221b24	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	I had an unforgettable experience with Explorandes on the Inca Trail in December. From start to finish, their team demonstrated impeccable organization, warmth, and expertise. Every detail was thoughtfully handled, making the journey both manageable and memorable.\n\n1. Pre-Trip Support\nThe Explorandes team reached out well before the trip to coordinate pick-up and answer questions. Our guide, Wilber, even came to our hotel the night before to share insights on the trail and give tips, which put us at ease and got us excited for the adventure ahead. They provided us with backpacks for the items carried by their team, which made the hike much more comfortable since we only needed a small day pack with essentials like water.\n\n2. The Journey Itself\nThe trail begins in a scenic valley and winds through diverse landscapes, taking us through forests, high altitudes, and valleys with stunning Inca sites and mountain views. Wilber was outstanding, sharing historical context and fascinating facts along the way, which enriched our appreciation of each site. One of the most breathtaking sections was the climb to Warmiwanusca (4215m) and the descent through areas filled with colorful orchids, adding a magical touch to the landscape.\n\n3. Cultural Enrichment\nWe interacted with local communities along the way and were introduced to traditional rituals to honor the "Apus" (sacred mountains). The team explained the ritual with coca leaves, and we even learned a few Quechua words. These touches created a deep sense of connection to the land and culture.\n\n4. Wildlife & Scenic Beauty\nWe encountered a rich variety of wildlife, from hummingbirds and butterflies to llamas and even a condor. The flora was equally impressive, with orchids and diverse plant species adding to the beauty of the trail. Each campsite was chosen for its stunning views, allowing us to camp near Inca sites and enjoy the sunrise over breathtaking landscapes.\n\n5. Comfort & Facilities\nGiven the challenging nature of the hike, I was grateful to only carry a small day pack, with Explorandes handling the rest. Each evening, our tents were set up for us, complete with sleeping bags provided by Explorandes. Meals were a delight – breakfasts were varied, and lunches were packed to enjoy along the trail with scenic views. For lunch and dinner, their chef would set up a kitchen in nature, serving multi-course meals (always an entrance, main course and dessert). A favorite snack was the tequeños with guacamole, which we asked for repeatedly! Additionally, they provided a portable toilet for convenience, and we even had showers on the first night and a chance to swim in the river mid-hike.\n\n6. Machu Picchu Arrival\nOur arrival at Machu Picchu through the Sun Gate was the perfect finale, just as the Incas would have seen it centuries ago. The views of Machu Picchu from above were surreal, and the sense of accomplishment and awe was beyond words.\n\nWhile we had a few cloudy moments (it was December, so the rainy season), the views, cultural experiences, and care from the Explorandes team made it an incredible journey. I highly recommend this adventure with Explorandes – it was challenging but filled with beauty, and the team made it a once-in-a-lifetime experience.\n\nThank you Wilber and Explorandes Team for such an experience, definitely see you soon!	Gilda fernandez-concha	5
19eeb6e7-877a-42ce-9378-000be45e4b08	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	Excelente lugar de almacenamiento de equipos de,aventura	Ceferino Alvarez	5
0f565cf2-ff9d-43bd-a6eb-5fe975aa81b8	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	Experience of a Lifetime\n\nOur trip was absolutely incredible! I was fortunate to connect with Luisa, who organized everything perfectly. She really understood what my family and I were looking for and crafted a trip that exceeded our expectations. We spent several days in the Sacred Valley, immersing ourselves in outdoor activities and making the most of every moment.\n\nThe Short Inca Trail is something I highly recommend to everyone. A special shoutout to our guide, Neptali, whose empathy and deep knowledge of the Incas truly made this experience unforgettable. It was the trip of a lifetime!\n\nI couldn’t recommend this company more. I only wish they organized trips to other destinations as well—if they could replicate these experiences elsewhere, I would definitely book more adventures with Explorandes.	Juan Martin Lopez	5
ca21c941-45b5-4004-b29c-d463c3b605ae	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	We did the 5D/4N Inca Trail to Machu Picchu plus 3 days in the Sacred Valley for acclimation before the big hike and another full day and 2 nights in Cusco before flying out.\n\nOriginally we had planned to go in 2020 with another couple but the pandemic forced us to postpone the trip until this year. By then we had convinced other family and friends to go and we ended up being a group of 9 in a private tour with Explorandes.\n\nThe itinerary was very well set up with time to acclimate in the Sacred Valley, the 5-day Inca Trail adventure with plenty of time to visit Machu Picchu and the final day touring Cusco. Explorandes office staff were very helpful and informative throughout the planning and booking process. Staff on the ground - drivers, folks helping us with airport transfers, checking into flights, etc. - were also most helpful.\n\nThe staff on the Inca Trail from the porters to the cooks to our guides were absolutely amazing! Miguel, our main guide, was unbelievably great. He was a wealth of information about the trail and the pre-columbian history and culture. He was warm, funny, very patient and always made us feel like we were his top priority. His command of English (and Italian!) was excellent! Elena was also a great assistant guide, always making sure we were taken care of an no one was being left behind.\n\nWe were amazed by the quality of the food on the trail, the quality of the camping equipment and the staff. How can they cook some really good pasta at 9,000 feet?\n\nThe hotels chosen by Explorandes and that were all part of the package were amazing. A very luxurious hotel in the Sacred Valley, a good hotel in Aguas Calientes (Machu Picchu) and a fantastic hotel in Cusco.\n\nI could not recommend Explorandes more. They will make sure you have a wonderful experience. The Inca Trail is very challenging, specially for a group like ours where many of the participants were over 60. But the Explorandes staff made sure that we could make it through and have a lot of fun in the process.\n\nThank you for an amazing experience, Explorandes!	Luis Valente	5
11b96eae-c491-445f-9081-d20970b4fc39	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	If you are looking to travel to Peru. Please consider the company that lead the first travellers down the Inca trail back in the 1970’s. They are first in experience and will take good care of you whether your on the hiking group or the personal guided tour of Machu Picchu as well as all the major sites. We are being guided as I write this halfway through a two week trip and feel thankful that we chose ExplorAndes. All our guides are so knowledgeable, hotels well chosen and the drivers have been very safe (given the traffic in Lima or the rural routes). We had some meals included but not all dinners were in case we were not wanting a big meal at night. Top tip: Learn what to tip the bellboy, guides, drivers and at restaurants in Sols.\n#ExplorAndes,	K F	5
7d0de0bb-f24d-4578-88b5-d6538615dfb3	cmp239xdl0013ml2uu20qkypz	We used Explorandes for a 4-day Inca Trail hike with a tour of Machu Picchu and a follow-up tour of Palcoyo (rainbow mountains). We were fortunate to have Carlos as our guide for the total of six days, together with fabulous cook Gabriel and an amazing team of porters on the four-day trek. Information provided prior to our departure was complete and helpful to set expectations and help pack effectively. Carlos was incredibly informative and friendly throughout the journey, giving us the history and background of the region, the trail itself, and the many historic sites we visited. He and the team emphasized safety and hygiene and were able to secure a private campsite the first night and excellent locations in group campsites for the other two nights. The camaraderie of the team made it clear that Explorandes treats its people well. We can't recommend Explorandes (and Carlos) highly enough, we will use them again in our next adventures into the Andes.	Mike Panzitta	5
