e21d76b0-2a71-495f-a1aa-abcc24a39b39	cmp239xf0001rml2ud8ejitnr	I probably wouldn’t recommend this tour. There was me, a girl, and 4 other boys on the tour. One of the boys bike broke down half way through so they had to ride together. I booked with the option to ride the quad bike solo which is more expensive than if you choose to ride 2 people together, but upon arrival I found out that I had to have the tour guide on the back of my quad bike with me the whole time. I already thought it was weird he picked me, the only girl, when there were four other boys which would have been more decent. During the route he kept asking me questions about my age and if I was single which was quite annoying. I asked him why he couldn’t ride his own quad bike and he said it’s because it’s broken but there were many quad bikes/motor bikes in the garage. He also asked if he could hold my waist and I told him that shoulders is better. He then said he was scared of falling so I asked if he’d rather go with one of the boys and he was adamant on staying on the bike with me. Anyway it was just a bit annoying because I paid the full price to ride alone but instead had some man asking intrusive questions on the bike with me the whole time.\n\nNot only this, you have to pay 5 soles directly to the guide to park next to a lake for 15 minutes which seemed ridiculous.\n\nAnyway the route was lovely.	Kierra Louise	1
