fe78574b-7b7c-46db-b1bc-1abf53c02b46	cmp239xe2001bml2uo8qx5uf5	A fantastic stay at El Albergue! We actually initially visited a few days before check in, when going to MP as we were keen on the coffee experience. Erik and his colleague helped book us on the experience today which was fantastic today with Bruno and Judith who went through the process of all coffee roasting and made us a delicious filter coffee as well. I learnt so much!\n\nThe breakfast is delicious here as most comes from their farm. The only thing I would ask is if meat is possibly kept separate container/lids to veggies where possible (but this is common in South America. We had some eggs made to order. I didn't get the lady's name who looked after us but she was very helpful , so thank you!\n\nRooms are very cool especially overlooking the trains and being part of the station. It can be a little loud when the come but they didn't run at night. The rooms are a little older fashion (for the one we stayed in) but possibly this is due to regulations being part of the station itself. Location is fantastic being in the station\n\nHighly recommend people who stay here utilise one of the experiences (theres a Pachamanca experience which looks very cool)\n\nThanks all for the lovely stay it is very unique	Jitesh	5
47d41712-308c-4b00-8cb2-a4960428ea6a	cmp239xe2001bml2uo8qx5uf5	O lugar para se hospedar em Ollantaytambo. Ambientes aconchegantes, confortáveis, com decoração elegante e atendimento diferenciado. As refeições sao saborosas e há atrativos que tornam o lugar especial, como sua horta orgânica e a escola para crianças. A passagem para a trilha até as ruínas é excelente, nao deixem de utilizá-la.\n\nRecomendo!	Roberto Sasaki	5
2b166a90-d2f8-4a85-93e6-e89862295e85	cmp239xe2001bml2uo8qx5uf5	This place was hands down my favorite that we stayed at in Peru. The feel of the it was so unique (rustic and authentic), and everything from the food, the service, to the location was just awesome. It's right by the train station, so if you're going to Machu Picchu, it's very convenient to just walk out the door and go, but it's so quiet and you really don't hear the trains when you're inside your room. The grounds themselves are vast, so you can walk around see the farm, distillery, etc and forget you're right near a busy town and train station. The food at the restaurant and the coffee at the cafe were phenomenal, I would recommend them to anyone. Thanks for a great stay!	Marie Argyriou	5
