62f296fd-ea6b-4362-a3d7-9510eaec3a0f	cmp1oj69t000fmllqxy44xbsw	Beautiful serene setting, artistic food presentation, impeccable and sincerely welcoming service, and most importantly, delicious. What a treat.  Very reasonable (I come from SF where a comparable fine dining meal may cost upwards of $60 without drinks). My friend and I lucked out as we did not have reservations, but we were on the early end (before 6 pm). This was our first meal in this beautiful city, and a more welcoming one after a long day of travel, I can’t imagine. We got a seat overlooking the plaza. My friend loved her osso buco. I loved my vegetarian choices, croquettes and an extraordinary hummus dish with braised carrots and fresh greens. Our chosen dessert was a standout, cocoa ice cream with brownies and caramelized nuts served in a cocoa bean shell — extremely generous portion for two already-full diners. Note: 10% - 15% tip is suggested for fine dining in Peru — the Morena wait staff definitely deserve this appreciation.	joyce ycasas	5
