af9e1270-e0dd-4d7a-a960-b9a1e604e081	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	Foram 4 dias no vale sagrado na excelente  companhia do Manuel (motorista) e do Adrian (guia).\nO conhecimento notável da história e cultura por parte do Adrian é assinalável e faz toda a diferença.\nA qualidade das refeições, quer em restaurante como em box é muito acima da média para este tipo de tours.\nA qualidade e principalmente a limpeza da viatura são excepcionais.\nE claro a simpatia e a preocupação de ambos  não tem preço.	Sandra Tavares de Carvalho	5
71529bf3-1448-4091-b30e-237f1300041b	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	Just completed the Classic 4-days Inca Trail with View Peru. Our guide Sebestian is knowledgeable in history, culture, plants and birds. It is more than a trek but an experience in all Peru’s history, culture and nature can offer. The gourmet food along the way prepared by Chef Zenon was fantastic and our massage therapist Iade really soothe our aching muscles at the end of the day with her healing hands. Our young Assistant Tour Guide Eber was also super helpful. All in all, it has been a very rewarding experience for my wife and me. Definitely recommend View Peru to organise Inca Trail for anyone who wants to have a great time on the trail.	Tom Goh	5
77ce8306-254c-4c09-a12c-0ddbb05f49f0	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	Adrián and his crew were absolutely incredible. The attention to detail and the care for their guests at all times was superb.\nYou could tell this company was far superior from all of the other guiding companies we encountered along the way. The luxury tents, cozy blankets, delicious sheets and decadent food, made this arduous and challenging trek a joy. The knowledge on the sites we visited was vast. We are already planning another trip for next year. Thank you!	stefanie prentiss	5
09f75c52-47a6-483b-ba25-90e9da670259	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	A journey of discovery through Cusco and Machu Picchu that became truly unforgettable thanks to the outstanding work of the entire View team — with special mention to Adrian and Manuel, whose dedication and professionalism were simply remarkable. My sincere gratitude to all of you. Thank you!	José Beleza	5
d15df52a-a4f7-4607-91c1-dc6aa9b790d7	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	Our Supreme Luxury Inca Trail to Machu Picchu trip booked through The View Signature Travel with our talented  guide Tomas and our 2 assistant guides, Yhon, and Henry was spectacular! The depth of knowledge of the flora, birds, history, and Andean culture was such a gift.  My husband and I were overwhelmed by the care and attention that our entire team provided for our journey. The hike is difficult, but perfectly orchestrated with breaks and "lessons."  All three of our guides picked up on my love of birds and flowers and my husbands interest in the architectural details of the Incan ruins and went above and beyond expecations to call birds and explain things in detail.  We were encouraged and taken care of through out the journey.  Honestly, I am a hiker, but this was a true challenge and the tips we received along the trail made it possible to complete the trek!\n\nThe food!  The meals along the trail deserve an entire review!  It is absolutely amazing what the team is able to do along this rugged 26 mile trail!  Nemesio and Fabian created exquisite 3 course meals that were varied and unique!  The flavors were wonderful and we all enjoyed every meal.  Our waiter Mauro was so friendly and helpful - the three of them delighted us with their talent! We even had a fully decorated baked cake!  I have no idea how they did it!\n\nWhen you  first read about "Supreme Luxury," it sounds wonderful!  Then you get out there on the trail and realize how remote you truly are and the comforts we are accustomed to living with on a daily basis like running water, flushing toilets, electricity, heat, and lights are no longer available.   However, your team of  Angels (porters) manage to bring  Supreme Luxury into each campsite.  It is absolutely remarkable.  You arrive tired and weary to cheers and joyful faces encouraging you and welcoming you to your home for the night.  Such care went into making everything perfect for our arrival and we felt like we really were welcomed home by family.  Hilario and our lead porter Anastacio seemed to be anxiously awaiting our return to the family at each site and genuinely please that we made it safely to camp!!  My husband and I were so grateful for all the people that were there simply to help create this experience for us!! Our massage therapist, Marianela was so skilled.  After the second day (the "hardest" day) we arrived exhausted, weary, and wet to our campsite.  The temperature dropped  and the rain was relentless - but Mari was ready and provided deep tissue massage and such a calming and recentering atmosphere that we were actually able to relax and release some of the stress from a long day of hiking.  She even found a way to dry my bedding that  was soggy from a tent mishap!\n\nYou will learn a great deal about the culture and the people as you walk the trail. Our guide, Tomas was a fanstaic teacher and spoke with great enthusiasm and passion about his own experiences,  history, culture and the trail. His passion was contagious!     Constantino and Santiago gave us a meanful presentation at dinner one night explaining indigenous traditions.  We learned some words in Quechua and learned a great deal about the Incas and their civilization. The Quechua people are the decendants of the Inca Empire and we loved learning from our guides and our team about their traditions.  Our hearts were overwelmed by their love of our Mother Earth and their deep pride for their culture, country, and history.\n\nMatt and I recommend The View Peru - Signuture Travels 100%\n\nWe had the best sites at each camp site, the best food, the most care and our 3 guides were the best you can imagine.  There is no room for improvement.  Absolute perfection from each and evey person on the team.  We are so thankful that we were able to experience Peru with all these wonderful and dedicated people.	Rebecca Hudson	5
1fe90bfc-3edf-4a1d-8a58-fdf46cc91579	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	We had an amazing experience on our Inca Trail hike thanks to View Peru! Starting from before our trip began, Javier was very helpful with all pre-trip coordination and making sure we were well prepared for our time in Peru. The hike itself was incredible, led by our guides Adrien and Fernando who were extremely kind, well-informed, and great cheerleaders to make sure our hike was a success. The amenities provided throughout were also impeccable, with top notch food served from our chefs Wilfredo, Julio and Abraham, beautiful and comfortable accommodations from our lead porter Jesus, and relaxing/revitalizing massages from Madeline. The entire experience was a well oiled machine that made our hike unforgettable! Absolutely recommend View Signature Travels	John Taylor	5
ed7e33f3-e67f-4801-ac6d-d3af07e17572	cmp239xe6001dml2u221298dk	The View Peru experience was incredible. End to end luxury, comfort, and kindness. Thomas, Bruce and team made us feel safe and capable and truly connected us with the experience of the Inca Trail. The sites are truly spectacular, and the team helped us capture so many amazing moments through pictures. The team knows the trail, the campsites, the nature, the history, the culture to really provide a complete and seamless experience.	Nisha Doshi	5
