359b9602-2024-443f-b10e-076dd38099fe	cmp239xed001gml2uz9soaatl	Machu Travel Peru organized an amazing trip to Machu Picchu and the Sacred Valley for me and my 21 year old son. They were able to accommodate all of our requests during the planning process, and were extremely responsive to questions.  They have options to meet a variety of budgets and interests. For example, I wanted 4 or 5 star hotels, to hike the short Inca trail into Machu Picchu and to take the Hiram Bingham train one way out of Machu Picchu.\n\nShortly before we arrived, we had a WhatsApp group with an operations team for any questions that arose.  The logistics were extremely well organized, including that we only took a small bag to Machu Picchu (which was taken from the train to our hotel in Agua calientes while we hiked) and our larger suitcase was transported from Ollataytambo to our hotel in Cuzco. It was all seamless and effortless for us.\n\nWe had the same driver (Wilfredo) and guide (Adolfo) for our whole time there. Both were anazing and focused on ensuring we enjoyed our trip. Adolfo was incredibly knowledgeable and personable, and we learned a lot without it seeming like a canned speech. He also accommodated that I needed a little extra time on some of the stairs/ascents on the hike and in the ruins. 😊\n\nI was a bit nervous about using a company that I found online, but the positive reviews convinced me to take a chance. It was an amazing experience from start to finish. I recommend Machu Travel Peru without reservation for a truly amazing experience!	Katherine Ritchey	5
