c3484025-48a0-4234-a77c-42fc743d476e	cmp239xi10035ml2u0drlzxze	Just a couple of guys who are really passionate about coffee. They spent time with us showing us around the space, sampling coffee (including one from José's farm), and talking about coffee. They buy nothing but high-grade specialty coffee, everything is grown 1500m+ and locally sourced from Puno and Cusco, fair trade. I wanted to bring a Kg home with me, but they're an exporter first and didn't have the bean I wanted available roasted, so I took a sample pack instead. 100% worth the trip out to see them!	Cory Funk	5
ebae2ab0-2ab5-4064-9314-49e45dadf6ad	cmp239xi10035ml2u0drlzxze	The place is a lab for coffee roasting and tasting. They welcome visitors, with out without appointment. Better if you make appointment - via instagram. Frank and Jose were very kind to share their time, give us a tour and let us taste different coffee roasts they were working on. They also sell a 4 sample pack at the store, but only cash PEN or cash USD accepted. They export green beans to US, China, UK, Australia. They also hold Fair Trade and Organic certifications. The source coffee locally from farms in Cusco, Puno and other regions of Peru.\nIf you like good coffee, this is an offbeat experience.\nThey are on the way from Urubamba to Calca in Urco. Grab a collectivo from Urumbamba and ask the driver to drop you at their doorstep.	Namita Chaudhary	5
