9c3707ee-7671-4bbf-b742-61b05dcc3f00	cmp239xi80038ml2u9wpzogvz	This place was hands down my favorite that we stayed at in Peru. The feel of the it was so unique (rustic and authentic), and everything from the food, the service, to the location was just awesome. It's right by the train station, so if you're going to Machu Picchu, it's very convenient to just walk out the door and go, but it's so quiet and you really don't hear the trains when you're inside your room. The grounds themselves are vast, so you can walk around see the farm, distillery, etc and forget you're right near a busy town and train station. The food at the restaurant and the coffee at the cafe were phenomenal, I would recommend them to anyone. Thanks for a great stay!	Marie Argyriou	5
