bf10276a-c50c-4842-971e-eddd2c418672	cmp1qmbke000wml5xa59z5rfl	Absolutely amazing! You walk in and it's like being in the seventies, just a very warm and homey interior with earthy colors contrasted with bright floral and psychedelic images. Really cool and happy place. They have ample seating space inside, filled with table games and dioramas, as well as outdoor seating in the front of the restaurant and in the back. So, about the back, that is where we sat and it was very lovely looking down onto the river, and the trees beyond, but keep in mind that in the evenings it gets pretty cold AND the river is very loud. When we go back (and I really hope we do) I would prefer to sit inside.\n\nMichael was taking care of us, and he did a terrific job recommending the dishes and he was very knowledgeable about the type of ingredients that were used in them. He was very professional and attentive.\n\nThe food was delicious and beautifully presented. As they said, it was made with love. Every element was perfectly positioned for the optimal appeal and esthetic value. Literally, it was a shame to eat it...\n\nTrucha con Champinones was PHENOMENAL. I am putting it in capital letters, because it deserves to be noticed. All the flavors perfectly balanced, all the components perfectly prepared and the presentation was a work of art. The trout was pink, cooked to perfection with crispy skin and delicate flesh. It was topped with tasty mushrooms in white, creamy sauce and accompanied with creamy, velvety mashed potato and saute vegetables. It was one of the best dishes I ever had, and I am a foodie. I would give this delectable creation a 15 out of 10.\n\nCausa did not look like its photo on the menu, but it was delicious. Three stacks of tasty chicken salad on the bed of thinly sliced avocados and potatoes in huancaína sauce. Served with edible flowers - we ate all of it!\n\nChupe de trucha did not impress me. It was hearty, but I believe that the tomatoes used in the sauce or during the cooking, gave too much acidity to the dish and took away the flavor of the fish. It created a bit of a sourness that distracted from the rest of the ingredients. This is only my personal opinion, so I feel that if it had more cream and way less tomato, it would bring out the trout's natural essence.\n\nWe indulged in a bit of Mulled Wine, which was lovely.\n\nOverall, excellent food, excellent service and great ambiance. There were so many dishes on the menu that I wanted to try! So sad that humans only have one stomach and it can only hold so much... I would love to come back for more.	Masha Kalmanovich	5
