e0c34c97-3d8b-4631-a933-4b073b4e81f9	cmp239xim003eml2uu1z32oyu	EXPERIENCIA DESACONSEJADA\n\nHicimos el camino inca de 5 días con esta agencia.\n\nHubo una gran diferencia entre los servicios contratados y la realidad. Para comenzar, nuestro guía, en el breefing nos dijo que teníamos que llevar más cosas de lo que realmente era necesario. A la mañana siguiente nos vinieron a buscar al hotel  pero a pie, ningún vehículo como estaba estipulado.\n\nTodo estaba orquestado para pagar extras. Pagamos los sacos de dormir, los bastones, el desayuno del primer día, etc...\nNos dieron unos sacos de dormir más pesados y grandes de lo que nos habían dicho. Por supuesto, nos los dieron a la entrada del trek para que no pudiéramos reclamar.\n\nNos tocó un guía que nos presionó para dejar propina durante el trek aunque en el contrato que firmamos estaba estipulado que  no era obligatorio. Todo parecía estar organizado para que pagáramos más dinero. Por ejemplo, si en un momento del trek, no podías con tu propia mochila, se nos ofrecía la posibilidad de pagar un extra para que los pórters llevaran nuestras mochilas a cambio de dinero. Ahí fue cuando empezamos a entender que todo se hacía para sacar más beneficio.\n\nEl itinerario fue el establecido pero los campings no. Los tiempos cambiaban constantemente en función de la improvisación del guía. Parece ser que estaba penalizado porque en el equipo el cocinero había infringido las normas varias veces y los clientes pagamos por los abusos cometidos. Peores campings, distancias recorridas que no eran razonables ni como se estipulaba en el contrato y, en consecuencia, toma de riesgos innecesarios.\n\nPor ejemplo, nos prometieron un camping cerca de la puerta del Sol. Finalmente dormimos tan lejos que tuvimos que comenzar a caminar a las 3 de la mañana, de noche y sin comer. Agotados, llegamos al sitio arqueológico con prisa y con poquísimo tiempo para visitarlo. También contratamos la subida al Wayna Picchu y nos perdimos la mayor parte de las explicaciones. En realidad fue una suerte puesto que, Lío, nuestro guía, nos explicó más cosas sobre el descubridor del sitio arqueológico que sobre la propia cultura inca...\n\nLas tiendas de campaña y los sacos estaban en malas condiciones y nuestros sacos se mojaron. (Se puede ver en las fotos).\n\nHicimos una reclamación en la tienda física donde explicamos con detalle todos los problemas que tuvimos. Nos dijeron que iban a estudiar nuestro caso. Lo último que nos dijeron fue que nos iban a reembolsar 50$.  Actualmente, casi un año después, me bloquearon de WhatsApp y jamás me reembolsaron.\n\nEn conclusión: más vale pagar un poco más y tener material, condiciones y guías adecuados que ahorrarse un poco de dinero y ponerse en riesgo.\n\nNO VAYÁIS A ESTA AGENCIA.	Aladino Pazo Paredes	1
dd168d6e-6024-4864-96c2-4ef76486fec8	cmp239xim003eml2uu1z32oyu	We did the 4D-3N Inka trail hike with this company and had an amazing experience. We are both vegan and I CANNOT stress how amazing, abundant & varied the food was! Some of the best catering I have ever had in my life, even including some tvp/soy protein! I miss it still. Our guide Raúl was very helpful & knowledgeable. We did the trek in March, we were very lucky that the rest of the group cancelled and it was just me and my partner so it was like a private tour. We did not have too much rain, although we did arrive to Machu Picchu in the mist on the final day so we did not get the classic photo, although it was still amazing to visit. We had booked the climb to Huayna Picchu, so we were able to see a clear panoramic view of Machu Picchu a bit later in the day (I really recommend this, especially if you go in the rainy season for a second chance to see Machu Picchu from afar). The porteadores were also friendly and helpful.	I'm Alexia	5
f1afbb5d-5bdd-4201-8a2c-a614053e3bf1	cmp239xim003eml2uu1z32oyu	We just finished the Inka trail (March 2026). We loved every bit of the tour and our guide Percy was amazing, very knowledgeable, funny and helped us on every part of the trip. We learnt so much and the tour at Machu Picchu at the end was one of the best. The food we had from Julio Caesar was also very good. Thank you!	Louise Hoblyn	5
afb3dbf4-084e-4f69-b416-e06887b983c1	cmp239xim003eml2uu1z32oyu	DO NOT BOOK WITH THEM. I bought a Machu Picchu tour for 9 people from them on January 10th for a trip in April. I sent them an $1800 deposit which turned out to be $1908 after credit card fees. On February 25th they reached out and told me that they could not get us tickets to Machu Picchu…. Almost 2 MONTHS after we had booked it. This was not a small trip we already booked our flights to Cusco, air bnbs, for 9 people. They claim there was a system error when they went to buy tickets for us and their payment was not accepted. Again almost 2 months after I had paid them did they tell me. I demanded my $ back and they tried dictating when they would send the money back and said it had to be through PayPal. After they sent the money back we ended up only getting $1694 back after MORE fees so we lost $214 not including the thousands in airfare + air bnbs and received NOTHING. Horrible experience, very unprofessional, I highly recommend booking through a different agency so you don’t risk this happening to you.	Lucas Martin	1
e4ccc24a-80cd-4ab1-b7cb-131ae1757805	cmp239xim003eml2uu1z32oyu	I would definitely not recommend booking here! Worst experience of my trip to Peru. I had booked a 5-day Salkantay Trek here. The evening before, the tour was canceled very spontaneously. I was promised that I would get my deposit back, minus the costs for the Machu Picchu ticket, which they already bought. I waited almost a week for the money, because I then spontaneously booked the trek with another company and was promised that the money would be sent to me via PayPal. However, this did not happen. Apparently, there were complications due to the rain. After that, there was no response to my message. When I went to the office in person a week later, they continued to try to fob me off. After a discussion lasting over 30 minutes, I finally got my money back. Very unpleasant and unsympathetic!!!! I had the feeling that they were just waiting until I left Cusco and no longer had a chance to collect the money. In addition, the Salkantay trek with this company includes a Machu Picchu ticket for circuit 3, which unfortunately does not offer the beautiful view from above.	Lisa	1
