5e726543-92dc-4790-82e0-60a7f873b301	cmp1q9rx90003ml5xbhfld0oc	The hostel had a very cool and artsy vibe throughout. The staff, especially Amir at the front desk, were all very friendly and accommodating, and granted last-minute changes to my booking. There are plenty of common areas to rest and meet other travellers. It’s around 5 minutes from the train/Consettur bus station but it’s definitely a bit of a hike up.\n\nThe rooms were just serviceable. For my room in particular, lockers were at the end of each bunk and seem only to fit a medium-sized backpack. The sliding door also came apart when I tried to close the locker. The beds were comfortable enough for tired travellers albeit slightly bouncy. The en suite bathroom had no ventilation, so the whole room would get stuffy or smelly depending on what you do in there. Everything seemed clean enough though so I didn’t feel too uncomfortable during my stay.\n\nThe breakfast was rather underwhelming, it was 15 soles for scrambled egg, cheese, tomato, and two cold croissants. Unless you need to have breakfast at 4:30am, there are probably better places in town for breakfast.\n\nThere was also some renovation going on in April 2026 so there were drilling sounds even at around 9pm.\n\nIn conclusion, convenient for short stays but might get unpleasant for longer stays.	Himson Ng	4
