ca4f67fd-9c32-4315-8cca-147904ffc700	cmp239xdg0011ml2u5w5apxru	A Life-Changing Experience, Deeply Healing and Beautifully Held!\n\nI recently attended this ayahuasca retreat that has truly changed my life. From the start, the team put incredible thought into preparing us for the ceremonies. The workshops are thoughtfully curated to give you the tools and mindset to enter the experience feeling ready, grounded, and open. Everything is designed with intention.\n\nWe had powerful sessions exploring childhood trauma and identifying our trauma responses, which gave me a deep understanding of my emotional patterns. Another workshop around victimhood helped shift my perspective and reclaim my personal power. We also had group-building workshops that created a real sense of safety and connection, making it easier to open up and share authentically throughout the week.\n\nNina’s yoga sessions are a highlight. Gentle, grounding, and always adapted to the group’s needs. Her deep presence and intuition extend into the music she curates for the ceremonies. The sound journey she creates is powerful, striking a perfect balance between being emotionally moving and deeply enjoyable. It acts as a beautiful guide throughout the experience.\n\nBefore the ceremonies, you also have access to wonderful bodywork like massages to reconnect with yourself, which I found incredibly helpful. There are even laundry services for those arriving from long travels. These small touches make a big difference in feeling at home and supported.\n\nDuring the ceremonies, Hector’s presence brings a strong sense of safety and calm. His experience is clear, and his gentle guidance, especially around the first hour mark or the booster time, makes you feel held and cared for throughout the journey.\n\nLais takes care of everything behind the scenes with such attention and kindness. If you have a logistical issue or feedback, she’s there to ensure it’s taken care of immediately. And then there’s Miro, whose spontaneous conversations somehow always land with clarity and insight, helping you make sense of your journey in subtle and profound ways.\n\nThe food deserves a mention too, healthy, fresh, locally sourced, and absolutely delicious. You truly feel nourished on every level.\n\nThis retreat helped me process deep grief, become more aware of patterns in my life, and gain closure on past traumas. The environment, the people, and the structure created a container that felt incredibly safe, loving, and transformative.\n\nIf you're considering an ayahuasca retreat, I wholeheartedly recommend this one. It is not only deeply healing but also thoughtfully and beautifully facilitated from beginning to end.	aline neven	5
48e1bcae-d684-443b-8ca1-7d929bc6b110	cmp239xdg0011ml2u5w5apxru	This retreat was one of the most meaningful and well-organized experiences I’ve had. The setting was beautiful, the food nourishing, and the ceremonies and workshops were thoughtfully planned to support real inner work.\n\nThe Ayahuasca ceremonies were led with care and presence. I really appreciated how Hector created a sense of connection by calling us "family" and regularly checking in with us. Being able to sit under the stars during the night ceremonies was especially powerful. The workshops like Childhood Regression, Victimhood, etc. were also a key part of the process. They helped prepare the ground for deeper experiences during ceremonies and gave us tools to make sense of what was coming up. The yoga and breathwork added a lot as well, supporting both body and mind through the journey.\n\nThis retreat offers a rare and supportive space for personal healing and growth. It feels genuine and well held. Overall, it was a deeply valuable journey, and I’d recommend it to anyone ready to do honest, inner work and reconnect with themselves.	Soul Cartographer	5
f43cea3b-f245-428b-a060-6796adf09bf2	cmp239xdg0011ml2u5w5apxru	I would like to thank the staff for their caring and support throughout the whole retreat. They created an inspirational and safe place. I remembered their calm walk, as they were keeping an eye on us during ceremonies. It was a feeling of safety and comfort. Selection of songs during sessions, made up of both softer and harder ones maintained the right atmosphere. Especially songs from Hans Zimmer.\n\nI enjoyed the day ceremony outside in the garden the most. There was a moment when the long-accumulated anxiety and fears inside me seemed to fall away suddenly and I could’t stop laughing out loud for several minutes. It was a relief I hadn’t experienced in a long time.\n\nBesides ceremonies I really enjoyed the art sessions where I could express my insights. Yoga classes were really useful due to my lack of movement and I have learned that yoga isn’t just about physical stretching muschles but contains also other deeper aspects.\n\nAt one of the workshops I learned something new about the roles in victimhood triangle. There were a lot of useful info that you can integrate into your life after the retreat.\n\nOh and I have to mention the dishes, every meal was delicious despite being mostly vegetarian.\n\nThe whole retreat concept was well-tuned and I experienced an unforgettable week. Big thanks for that opportunity.	Lukáš Kaláth	5
