abad3d44-ea5c-496b-8f9f-477c716fc2d7	cmp239xdg0011ml2u5w5apxru	*About My First Trip Worth Taking from Europe to Universe.*\nIf your idea of a getaway is sipping cocktails while ignoring your inner demons, pretending to read a self-help book, this is NOT the place. But if you want to dive headfirst into the cosmic washing machine and come out (mostly) clean on the other side — welcome to the most transformative experience of your life, and thus, the best ayahuasca retreat ever!\n\n*Nature? More Like Heaven’s Backyard.*\nImagine waking up to misty mountains, birds singing like there is no tomorrow, and sunsets so gorgeous they made me question why I ever looked at a phone screen. The jungle was alive, the river was sacred, and the stars? Let’s just say I finally understood why people write poetry.\n\n*The Service? Flawless – Like Being Wrapped in a Spiritual Blanket. *\nFrom arrival to departure, the staff treated us like queens and kings. And the organizing Team balanced professionalism with the warmth of people who definitely know what it's like to see the universe fold into a taco during your experience. They anticipated every need — whether it was an extra cushion during ceremony, a reassuring word at 3 AM when Mother Ayahuasca showed you your childhood traumas in 4K...they’ve got you.\n\n*The Food? Way Too Good for a "Diet".*\nWhen I heard "retreat diet," I expected sad boiled vegetables and existential dread. But the chefs here are actual wizards. Every meal was vibrant, fresh, flavorful, organic and made my taste buds dance. 11/10 would eat again!\n\n*Workshops & Yoga: Because Tripping Alone Isn’t Enough.*\nBetween ceremonies, we had workshops and sharings that were equal parts profound, enlightening and also very fun. Morning yoga was the perfect way to realign my body after a night of some spiritual acrobatics. Not to mention the carefully crafted music used during night/day ceremonies and workshops which enhanced the whole experience 1000%\n\n*The Experience? Like a Cosmic TED Talk for Your Soul.*\nLet’s be real — ayahuasca isn’t a weekend hobby. It’s an emotional car wash where your soul gets the deluxe scrub, it's a deep dive into the ocean of your own consciousness. But with this retreat’s guidance, safety and love? It felt nothing like drowning and all like learning to swim with dolphins.\n\n*Final Verdict:* If you’re ready to face the cosmic mirror with amazing professional guidance of Miro and his Team, laugh-cry your way to clarity, and do it all surrounded by paradise and amazing humans—book this retreat. Just bring an open heart and a journal...\n11/10 – Would Soul-Search Again 💜🌿\n⭐🌑🌒🌓🌔🌕🌞🌕🌖🌗🌘🌚⭐	Michaela Úradníková	5
