2d6657c5-f3bb-4988-af0c-c15f27b31f34	cmp2bkr5e000lml8g9nom2igl	I had booked 3 reservations with this hotel back in June 2025, all for April 2026.  Over the past few weeks I sent them 3 separate emails, two messages through their website and a WhatsApp asking them to please confirm my reservations.  I could see on their website that they had allegedly been “closed for renovations” for about the past 5 months but it said they were planning to re-open April 1.  I never received a reply to any of those 6 requests.  Finally because I was out of options, I asked my local tour provider to call them to help me confirm.  The tour operator emailed back saying they had spoken to someone at El Balcon who said that they “were not operating”!\n\nTo say I as flabbergasted is an understatement.  El Balcon cared so little about me as a customer that there were going to allow me to show up on their front door on the night of April 12 and tell me that they were not open!!!  (Assuming someone would have even BEEN there to say that).    This is just beyond unethical.  I ended having to make last minute reservations at another Cusco hotel that will end up costing me $2000 more!\n\nWhether or not they re-open in April of not, I strongly encourage anyone thinking about booking here to not do so!  You may end up being left high and dry like I would have been had I not asked my tour provider to call them.\n\nShame on you, El Balcon!	minnbeef	1
