6aa0df38-9856-476b-bebc-ff02c944302c	cmp239xen001lml2up8rxoqgp	This was my first international travel in my life and it was so much more than I expected. John and Edwin shared their culture, knowledge and history of Peru, Inca ruins, Machu Picchu and so much more! Our trip was 11 days including 4 days on the Inca Trail. As a slow backpacker from the states it was so reassuring that John and Edwin continued to check on our group, how we felt, altitude symptoms and overall experience!  I learned about some of our porters how hard they work and was in awe of their athleticism because it takes strong individuals to carry the weight, leave after you and still be set up before you and provide everything you could need! Thank you John and team for looking out for your supporting team. Having 3 hot & fresh meals a day on a backpacking trip plus BIRTHDAY CAKE in the Andes Mountains....wow! So much to say but just WOW! Seriously, you will not regret your trip with Machu Picchu tours!	Jenn Jenn	5
