88ec50d1-39f9-486e-aa9c-6f7b0ba490fd	cmp2bluhc000pml8gj0gd71j6	My wife and I stayed at Monasterio in November 2024 before and after completing the Inca Trail, and it remains one of the most memorable hotel experiences we’ve ever had.\n\nSince then, we’ve travelled extensively and stayed in many other hotels, but to this day we still talk about our time at Monasterio. The service was impeccable, the grounds and rooms were immaculate, and it truly set the gold standard for what a five-star hotel should be.\n\nWhat really stood out were the little things like staff bringing a blanket for my wife without even being asked while she was sitting and reading in the courtyard. The breakfast buffet was delicious, and the staff were incredibly accommodating if you wanted a particular fruit or dish. We also appreciated the thoughtful gesture of a parting gift when we departed.\n\nAbsolute worth every penny, we talk about it to this day.	Ned	5
90f1dc40-d25f-4a31-9bff-91aae118e1fa	cmp208d54000nmlpoylehr85m	This place was life changing. The facilitators maybe it special beginning to end. They are 100% the spirit of this place and I cant thank each of them enough. The aya ceremonies was tough for me and my wife due to the smoke and I am still not sold on the maestro but I cant say enough good things about the facilitators, such wonderful loving human beings. They will always hold a special place in my heart. The huachuma maestro was also amazing and he is truly medicine for the soul. I pray they hold onto this wonderful group of people who help guide others selflessly and with such patience and love for a long time.	Ben Depuy	5
f5c5d64b-6d91-4244-876f-5c2b8c991748	cmp208d54000nmlpoylehr85m	I spent two weeks in sacred valley and my experience was amazing. I had a lot of things to work through so it wasn't always fun to work through but the staff, facilitators, chefs and are amazing groups made it life changing. Everyone is so kind and help you with just about anything. So thankful I chose Arkana Spiritual Center for my healing. Such a beautiful place and experience. Hard to put everything into words but I highly recommend them to anyone wanting to heal, grow spiritually orpause and reconnect with yourself. I will be back in the future and thanks again to everyone who were so wonderful and helped me with my healing/health and wellness journey!	jeremy roth	5
455654c5-0611-4496-8549-cb5d4fc45399	cmp208d54000nmlpoylehr85m	There is a place hidden deep in the Sacred Valley of the Andes Mountains, where before visiting, you must first clip out of bounds.  In this place, there is no time.  There is no space.  There is only Love.  This Love erases all potential space for things like fear, trauma, and resentment to exist within.  But beware: in order to get there, you must be willing to surrender everything.  I went there once.  The things I saw cannot be expressed in words, but this will have to do.\n\nOnce you pass through the gates of The Garden, you make a near-seamless transition into a state of being where time and space no longer behave as they did before.  The entrance is situated far away from where "the action" takes place.  This is significant because it means you no longer see or hear who comes and goes.  They all seem to appear in The Garden out of thin air, stay for a while, and dissolve back into the ether.   You did not know this person was going to be here.  You don't know how long they will stay.  You are just grateful to be with them.\n\nIn this place I met The Love Bug, The Mountain, The Warrior and The Siren.\nIf you are lucky, you can talk to a Love Bug that calls itself Sean. The Love Bug is kind and gentle.  His radiant center calls you closer to receive his wisdom.  You can also hug a Mountain called Cinzia. Her fearlessness lays a protective barrier around your heart and mind, which you will need if you are going to take this journey to its fullest extent.  If you think you are ready, you can inherit ancient technology from The Warrior (Matty B).  His presence is still and powerful. He is pure Brahman. He taught me everything I was willing to learn.  You can also be sung into dissolution by The Siren (Matty G).  If she is singing, it is best to not make eye contact with her.  There is a chance that her gaze may become fixed on The Warrior, and that gaze is not intended for mortal consumption.  Their music cradled me during times of war.\n\nAnd if you want, you can also sit with Mother Ayahuasca under the protection of The Conductors: Maestra Ada and Maestro Idael.  These Holy Beings have my complete and unadulterated trust.  Their presence looms over, under, and throughout The Garden.\n\nIn this place, I watched all of my false identities die a terrible death, one by one.  And just as I was about to scream for help, a voice asked "Who is it that is about to scream for help?"  It was at this moment that I touched the part of Myself that is indestructible.   The Field of Awareness that animates each of us, that has been carrying me through this incarnation.  This Awareness is Pure Light. It is self-luminous and pure. It is one without a second. To know it is to be Eternal.\n\nMy cup runneth over.\n\nTo the caretakers Bob, Logan, and Matt, though I could have done with more interaction with each of you, it is worth honoring the contributions you made to my experience at Arkana.  You are all living examples of how plant medicine can put one back in touch with their inner call to serve others.  I came here to deepen my compassion for others and to expand my spiritual practice. I did that, and more. Much more.  This "much more" includes drinking in panoramic views of the mountains and stars, a garden of true earthly delights, and connecting with nature in a way I never knew was possible.  I have never eaten cleaner or tastier food.  Thank you to the chefs and the grounds keepers.  I have never known purer Beings.\n\n"Push far enough towards the Void,\nHold fast enough to Quietness,\nAnd of the ten thousand things none but can be worked on by you.\nI have beheld them, whither they go back.\nSee, all things howsoever they flourish\nReturn to the root from which they grew.\nThis return to the root is called Quietness;\nQuietness is called submission to Fate;\nWhat has submitted to Fate has become part of the always so.\nTo know the always-so is to be Illumined;\nNot to know it, means to go blindly to disaster."\n\n-Dao De Jing	Good Henchman	5
7033341d-1639-4283-9973-6255e35bb01a	038dbf42-bf0c-4488-9db0-ced60c12aa31	Otro punto obligatorio de la ciudad de Cusco, el ingreso o boleto parcial para extranjeros cuesta 70 soles e incluye ingreso a otros sitios de interés de ka ciudad. Con el boleto general (130 soles) puedes ingresar a los sitios del tour del valle sagrado.\n\nBonita experiencia en estas Ruinas, vale la pena el recorridoncon guia para entender la dinámica de estos sitios. Si lo haces sin guía tambien es fácil realizar el recorrido	Andres Mauricio Caballero López	5
112f06ab-6e53-4ec8-b31e-9570cc5f94ac	038dbf42-bf0c-4488-9db0-ced60c12aa31	Amazing piece of history. For tourists, make sure you bring your tourist ticket as it is included. Guides can be found at the entrance if you don’t have one or if you decide to take a last minute guided tour.\n\nNote that there is a lot of walking to do within the compounds so please wear good shoes. The altitude is also pretty high at some parts (around 3600-3700m) so if you’re prone to lung/asthma issues or heart issues, you might want to reconsider limiting your steps. I only have lived on sea level throughout my life so any form of stairs and slopes were extremely tiring. At the highest point I couldn’t even speak due to the feeling of constantly being breathless.\n\nRegardless, the site was well-preserved. There are also mainly Inca steps so it is not recommended to have baby prams or wheelchair here	Gaby Tan	5
51e371ef-cb85-4cf5-b0bd-b20c9c9315e1	cmp239xea001fml2u6zi27m9q	What we experienced on the Inka Trail with Alpaka Expedition was so much more than a hike to Machu Picchu. It was a reminder of what really matters in life: community, hospitality, humility, beauty, and shared humanity.\n\nThe porters, led by Cesar, were incredible. They gave us the gift of carrying our weight…not just physically, but emotionally and spiritually as well. Because of them, we were able to breathe. To truly breathe on the sacred mountain that is their home. They created space for us to slow down, to put aside the noise and busyness of our lives, and to meditate on what is truly important. Their strength, kindness, work ethic, and joy were deeply moving. Watching them navigate the mountains with grace and dignity was one of the most humbling experiences of my life. Cesar led the team with quiet excellence, compassion, and pride.\n\nChef Alfredo pulled out all the stops. Every single meal felt impossible given where we were…fresh, beautiful, nourishing, and made with incredible care. He not only took care of all of our allergies and dietary needs flawlessly, he created moments of joy around the table every day. Each meal felt like both a sunrise and a celebration. But beyond the food, he gave us something even more meaningful: the gift of the table. A place where strangers became friends, where stories were shared, laughter echoed through the campsites, and memories were created that we will carry forever.\n\nJimmy and Carlos led the entire experience with extraordinary kindness, patience, wisdom, and generosity. They set the tone from the very beginning. Every detail was handled with care, every challenge met with calm encouragement, and every person made to feel seen and valued. They didn’t just guide us through the mountains…they helped create one of the most meaningful adventures I have ever had. Their love for the land, the history, and their people was contagious and inspiring.\n\nAnd in the end, what this team gave us was something far more valuable than reaching Machu Picchu. They gave us the gift of family. For four days and three nights, we laughed together, struggled together, ate together, learned together, and became something more than a tour group. We became a community.\n\nThis was truly one of the greatest experiences of my life, and I cannot recommend this team highly enough. 5 stars for Cesar and the incredible porters. 5 stars for Chef Alfredo. 5 stars for Jimmy and Carlos. 5 stars for the entire experience from beginning to end.\n\nI would highly, wholeheartedly recommend this journey to anyone considering the Inka Trail.	Mark Priddy	5
4e1a2563-e30e-442c-a51d-f4f377bf9625	cmp239xea001fml2u6zi27m9q	Just finished up my 4d/3n trek to Machu Picchu with Alpine Expedition and must say that AE and Machu Picchu were magnificent!!! Jhymy was the perfect guide as well as assistant guide Carlos. They were very informative. Ask for them if possible.\nAlfredo the chef was totally amazing with his creations and was very accommodating to everyone’s food needs. Ceaser was head of the porters and took great care of our gear and addressing any issues.  Long story short Alpaca Expeditions is LOCALLY OWNED AND GIVES BACK TO THE COMMUNITY SO PLEASE CHECH THEM OUT.	Dennis Goodrich	5
b03474ef-a482-4326-b146-e7a3a1dd0259	cmp239xea001fml2u6zi27m9q	My hiking experience was truly unforgettable . The entire team made the journey not only possible but enjoyable from start to finish . Huge thank you to porters led by Cesar. Their dedication behind the scenes deserves so much respect and appreciation. The Chef Alfredo was absolutely amazing .Every meal was fresh and delicious. It’s hard to describe how much warm and good food can lift your spirit after a long day of hiking . And finally our guides Jimmy and Carlos were exceptional : knowledgeable, patient, encouraging and very experienced. They made us feel safe and motivated throughout the hike while also sharing information about mountains, culture and environment.   Overall a very nice experience. Thank you to the entire team .	Anitha Krishnamurthy	5
944d4108-5a89-4fa2-8368-ba1526374156	cmp239xea001fml2u6zi27m9q	This was our girls trip which we were waiting for so long .Alpaca expedition team made it easy from start to finish .They go above and beyond to help us .\n\nThe porters Cesar and team were the heart of our Inca Trail experience. Their strength, dedication, and positivity amazed us every day.I am  deeply grateful for everything they did — carrying gear through challenging terrain while still cheering us on with smiles. They made this journey unforgettable.”\n\nA huge thank you to our Alfredo cook for taking such great care of my dietary preferences throughout the trek. I do not eat eggs, and he thoughtfully prepared special meals for me every day without making me feel limited in options. The food was delicious, fresh, and incredibly impressive considering it was cooked on the trail. His kindness, effort, and attention to detail made the experience so much more comfortable and enjoyable.”\n\nI especially appreciated how attentive and supportive our guide Jimmy And Carlos were  during the trek. Since I was managing some ankle discomfort, he regularly checked on me, adjusted the pace when needed, and made sure I felt comfortable and confident on the trail. That extra care meant a lot.”\n\nHighly recommend Apalaca expedition.	vidya annigeri	5
924e2236-8a07-459f-a472-a4c9b9439afb	cmp239xea001fml2u6zi27m9q	Best hiking expedition experience ever! Starting with our amazing guide Jimmy, who patiently explained everything from pre-hike orientation to every single day. Jimmy was accompanied by Carlos, both of them guided and guarded like our own family would at every step of the way. And food was delicious every meal and we celebrated two birthdays in our group and chef, Alfredo and team baked a delicious cake in the middle of nowhere. They were incredible at every meal and mindful of our dietary restriction. Last but never the least the porter team lead by Cesar who carried our baggage while we barely carried ourself through the 4 day hike. We are incredible grateful to this team. And in a heartbeat would recommend this team for Machu Picchu 4 day hiking tour with Alpaca Expedition!	Chetna Desai	5
