89aa9d1a-df54-47d0-8cab-33a2991111ed	df692be7-5351-4304-8ff1-ed468d52e0c8	Visiting the magical Samadhi had been a dream of mine for three years—and it finally came true. It was everything I had imagined and more. The love and care poured into this place by the owners, their friends, and family is evident in every thoughtful detail. It’s not just a destination—it’s an experience.\n\nWe stayed in the stunning two-story Earth House, complete with a private patio overlooking the mountains. Waking up each morning to that breathtaking view was pure serenity.\n\nThe food at Samadhi was nothing short of exquisite. Every meal exceeded our expectations—not just in taste, but in presentation and atmosphere. Beautiful, simple, and absolutely delicious, the meals quickly became something we looked forward to every day.\n\nThe coffee and juice shop added a delightful touch to the stay. I especially loved the chocolate-covered walnuts and pecans, as well as the creative selection of drinks and desserts—each one a treat.\n\nFabrizio and Eduardo were incredibly kind and attentive, adding warmth to our entire experience. Their presence truly made a difference.\n\nWe were lucky enough to enjoy a full moon fire ceremony, along with painting and pottery classes, and deeply relaxing massages. The yoga and class space is absolutely stunning—it felt like a sacred retreat, and I loved how easy it was to book it for personal use.\n\nThere are many beautiful places to visit in the world, but what sets Samadhi apart isn’t just the views or the amenities—it’s the feeling it leaves you with. At Samadhi, I felt truly welcomed and at home.\n\nI will absolutely be back. Thank you from the bottom of my heart to the staff for making our stay so special.	Yulia De La Mora	5
3e12bfa2-b83b-4cb0-8edb-b32d3bd77397	df692be7-5351-4304-8ff1-ed468d52e0c8	I had the privilege of staying at Samadhi for a retreat and training event March 5-25, 2025. The location is truly unique in the sacred valley, and the theme of the chakras and holistic well being is carried throughout the estate. Our group was a large one and the staff did their very best to accommodate all of us at the same time. The food was delicious, and incredibly fresh: literally garden to table! I spent a couple of hours during one of our days off using the materials in the art therapy room, which was perfect for a sometime artist like myself.\nI was in a double room which had a covered porch with table, chairs and comfy hammock. During our few breaks, I came to love swinging on the hammock, hearing the amazing loud drone of the large hummingbirds, and 'Bob' (the bird I named) who hung out on the nearby arch above the stairs to the dining area.\nThe chef(s) were so talented, and everyone on staff went out of their way to make us all feel comfortable, well fed, and warm as we were there during the wet and cool season. I felt a call to return home a few days early and Fernando assisted me in arranging for a car to pick me up at 5 a.m. to get to the Cusco airport, and everything went smoothly.\n\nThis retreat center and hotel is a gem-- everything about it is magical. I can't share enough gratitude to the staff and caretakers of this beautiful space. One evening we were dancing (our group of women) and we were able to invite in the daughter of one of the caretakers to join in with us. That kind of seamless, organic community is so incredibly special. Thank you, everyone at Samadhi, for taking such good care of me and our group during this past March. 💕🙏 I look forward to my return!!\n-Kristi Lee	Kristi Lee	5
