15ee304c-ed75-414e-a2a2-eabf45599c3d	174850f9-6e46-4780-bee6-9f571c8c3d9c	We spent two nights at Rumi Lodge in Pisac. We were warmly welcomed by Benito, the owner, who accommodated us in every possible way with kindness and a contagious smile. Although the lodge is not in the center of Pisac, it is well served by Tuk-Tuks, which take you anywhere in just five minutes for 5 soles. For 35 soles, a private car can take you to the entrance of the Pisac ruins. The breakfast was exceptional, the panoramic view unforgettable, and while the comfort was basic, everything necessary was provided—even hot water without a timer, which is not always a given. Don't be discouraged by the entrance, which is currently not the most inviting due to ongoing construction on the neighboring property (however, there was never any disturbing noise).\n\nTraducción al español:\nPasamos dos noches en Rumi Lodge en Pisac. Benito, el propietario, nos recibió con los brazos abiertos y nos atendió de todas las maneras posibles con amabilidad y una sonrisa contagiosa. Aunque el alojamiento no está en el centro de Pisac, está bien comunicado con los Tuk-Tuks, que por 5 soles te llevan a cualquier lugar en solo cinco minutos. Con 35 soles, un coche privado te lleva hasta la entrada de las ruinas de Pisac. El desayuno fue excepcional, la vista panorámica inolvidable y, aunque la comodidad es básica, tiene todo lo necesario, ¡incluso agua caliente sin temporizador! Lo cual no siempre es algo seguro. No se dejen desanimar por la entrada, que en este momento no es la más acogedora debido a la construcción en la propiedad vecina (sin embargo, nunca hubo ruidos molestos).	Matt	5
e9f8c935-987f-4513-9205-bf54e76dda2b	174850f9-6e46-4780-bee6-9f571c8c3d9c	Benito is such a friendly host! He’s not always around but when he is he is super super nice! He cares a lot and if you need anything he always helps you out! I spent there almost 2 weeks after dieta and it was perfect! The rooms are deluxe, such a comfortable and big bed, very beautiful and new design and amazing private bathroom. Outdoors is a garden areas (kind of 2 areas actually) & fireplace areas and you’re in between of the mountains and underneath a blanket of stars in the night - sooo beautiful! You can use the laundry machine. There’s a huge well equipped kitchen and even a dining room. It’s a natural nature place, quite calm and high standard!! Rooms are not fully isolated so especially in winter time bring enough warm clothes for the night. By foot it’s a 30 minute walk to town - along some eucalyptus trees & Mountain View :)\n\nThank you Benito for everything! 🙏	Ene Nena	5
