586563bf-f0e3-449e-8180-524d62f870f1	e2e883bd-534f-49e2-a96b-31186fa97955	💖Tranquility hotel is a friendly place with an excellent location!\n⭐️We first chose this place because of its central location and excellent reviews. Once we arrived, we felt it truly lived up to its name: the tranquility and vibe immediately help you calm down. The owners are incredibly kind. At one point, we tried to get to the Parque Arqueológico Pisac but couldn’t find an Uber. We turned to a young man at the front desk who knew the area well, and he helped us finally find the place to call a taxi.\n⭐️Another time, when we were checking out, my friend wasn’t feeling well. Since we speak very little Spanish, we were afraid of buying the wrong medicine and almost gave up on finding help. However, during breakfast, the lady asked about our situation, and her husband (the owner) went out personally to purchase the medicine we needed. He didn't even want us to pay for it at first, but my friend insisted and we finally checked the medicine at front desk.\n⭐️Apart from the people, the place is beautifully decorated. As soon as you enter, you feel the peaceful atmosphere. They offer free water and have some local products for sale. It is mentioned that the water can be unstable, but it is actually just a bit hard to adjust, as we can still have a warm shower without waiting too long. Moreover, we couldn't ask for more, since this is a small town hidden in the mountains and the staff are doing their best for the guests.\n⭐️The breakfast is also delicious. I started with a beautifully colored cup of coffee, followed by three pieces of bread with butter and two types of jam. I thought that was the whole meal, but I was surprised! After the bread, I was served scrambled eggs with avocado and a bowl of bananas and mangoes.\n💖We loved our stay here and would definitely recommend it to others! Also, please visit pisac when you feel hesitant because the place would never disappoint you.	Iris Chen	5
