27163e10-4b29-4d3d-be8b-d56993c0185a	e5dadc40-9f3c-4523-9cd4-4e106c550bf9	The views were stunning, the bedroom was comfortable and big, there was a huge soaking bathroom. Stairs up from the room led us to the dome on top for stargazing.\nThe service fell terribly flat. We were not offered a menu or an explanation that it was a set menu. The table next to us was offered a menu and ordered off it, we were just given food. When I asked what the other options are for dinner I was met with dismissiveness and was told “you said you had no restrictions.”\nThe table next to us didn’t want the soup so they just didn’t get an appetizer. All they would have had to do was say it was a set menu or that things had run out, but there was absolutely nothing.\n\nOverall, it is a beautiful and peaceful setting and the dome concept is very cool. Unfortunately, the experience didn’t match the expectations of the price point.	Fiona Crowley	3
