e1be96ef-9891-4e86-b3cc-405e645edeb4	e5dadc40-9f3c-4523-9cd4-4e106c550bf9	Where do I start with this place? I don’t think words are enough to praise it; you just have to visit! We were collected from hotel Casa Maria in town and the drive to Stardome was breathtaking. A taste of what was to come. Upon arrival, Alex the host gave us the most welcoming walk through the site. This included meeting the animals of the small farm of Stardome that included a curious and very cute llama, bunnies, ducks, chicks and a baby kitten we fell in love with. We also got to meet Carlos the owner who had such a warmth in his manner towards us and the animals one could see the love that has gone to every corner of this place. Alex took us to the Condor temple where we had a welcoming ceremony, a truly spiritual experience blessed with the most inexpensive shine. This property truly lives up to its name. We felt so grateful to have arrived to this incredible place. In our room there was a bowl of delicious strawberries from the garden.\n\nWe chose to have dinner included in our stay. Food and tea was plentiful. It was very taste but slightly overpriced. The star of the meal was a soup for me cooked with ingredients from the garden. Rain came later in the evening meaning we didn’t get to see the stars but the property literally felt located amongst the clouds. In the morning, the clouds cleared in time for breakfast which was delicious.\n\nIt was such a privilege to spend a night so close to nature, in this incredible spot! Our only regret was that we only had one night at Stardome.	Efi Ntoumouzi	5
