962d2350-cc41-47d9-ae5e-69a8e5825fa7	e5dadc40-9f3c-4523-9cd4-4e106c550bf9	We had a truly magical, soul-changing stay in the Star Dome. We actually planned our trip specifically to be there for the rare six-planetary alignment and the Blood Moon eclipse, and it turned out to be even more incredible than we imagined. The dome has an opening at the top so you can lie back and look straight into the night sky….watching the planets align above us was absolutely breathtaking. ✨\nAlthough the Blood Moon rose on the other side of Ollantaytambo and we couldn’t see it from the dome, the sky was still stunning and full of wonder.\nThe views are indescribable…you can see the town below and the vast mountains all around you. There’s such a peaceful stillness that it almost feels like the mountains are speaking. During our stay we made an offering to Mother Earth and even saw a condor soaring overhead, which felt incredibly meaningful.\nThe hospitality here is truly special. The new manager, Allie Mendoza, made our stay even more magical with her warmth and care. The staff welcomed us so kindly, showed us around the property, and shared beautiful ceremonies. We also had the opportunity to experience San Pedro with Friday, the coolest shaman and healer ever…it was a deeply profound experience.\nThe little details made everything even more special: the adorable animals and small farm, the amazing food (the trout was perfect every time!), Muña tea to help with the altitude, and even help with our laundry.\nThis place is more than somewhere to stay—it’s a place to reconnect with nature, the universe, and yourself. We left feeling blessed, grounded, and incredibly grateful!!	Holly Roska	5
