2087ef08-bb5d-4a88-8130-6cee82be13ee	8f2f473c-b1dc-4ab7-a6c3-7e484001d97a	We initially engaged Peru Spirit Adventures to assist us with securing Machu Picchu tickets, a process that appeared complex. From the outset, communication was excellent. Efrain responded to our inquiry the same evening and, since we had mentioned we were interested in suggestions for visits in the area during our stay, within a few hours, he proposed a tailored Sacred Valley Tour, Machu Picchu, Cusco & Chinchero to Urquillos Hike– 6D/5N itinerary with multiple options that reflected our preferences. His efficiency, responsiveness, and attention to detail were outstanding, and his rates were very reasonable given the level of service provided.\n\nThis private tour was an outstanding experience for us. Upon arrival in Cusco, we were personally greeted by Efrain and introduced to our driver, Michael. Over the following days, Michael proved to be exceptionally professional—punctual, courteous, and an excellent driver. His English proficiency was impressive, and his consistently positive attitude made our transfers both comfortable and enjoyable.\n\nWe were also fortunate to be accompanied by Anthony, our guide for the duration of our stay. Anthony demonstrated an extraordinary depth of knowledge about Peruvian history, culture, and traditions. His tours of Machu Picchu, the Sacred Valley, Cusco city, and the Urquillos hike were not only highly informative but also engaging and well-paced. His impeccable English, professionalism, and warm personality ensured that every aspect of our experience was seamless.\n\nWe loved the Chincherro to Urquillos day hike. It’s a less known portion of the Inca trail that offers stunning scenery and interesting Inca ruins.\n\nThanks to the combined efforts of Efrain, Michael, and Anthony, our trip was entirely stress-free. All logistics were managed with precision, allowing us to simply enjoy each day. Their professionalism and dedication far exceeded our expectations, and they seemed passionate about sharing their love for their beautiful country. We had an outstanding experience we will never forget, and learned so much about the history and culture of Peru. It’s also great to know that we are dealing with a locally owned business.\n\nWe would not hesitate to recommend Peru Spirit Adventures to anyone seeking an outstanding travel experience in Peru.	François Lajeunesse	5
