94d9ec54-bea1-45b7-9c40-f8616a01c31f	b1a92544-37a5-4337-89ce-8f2d26adeb4f	We had an amazing experience during our first trip to Peru. I worked with Carlos to plan and coordinate several tours/excursions and they were all excellent and curated to fit what we were looking for. We started with a trip to Machu Picchu, where the tickets, train and bus rides were coordinated and our guide, William was extremely knowledgeable and made sure we left Machu Picchu understanding the history and culture.\n​Our next excursion was the Sacred Valley tour where we were picked up by our driver Juan, who was excellent in navigating the rough terrain, and our guide William. During this tour we toured Ollantaytambo ruins, the Salt Mines and Moray. The highlight of the day was visiting Sonia and her family where an absolutely delicious lunch was prepared. This was a truly special part of the whole trip.\n​We also did a textile excursion where we visited Andean Colors, a special organization dedicated to helping single mothers who have faced great adversity leverage their textile expertise to support their families. We learned about plants, yarn dyeing, preparing the fiber and much more all set amidst stunning scenery.\n​Our last excursion was a hike up Palccoyo "Rainbow" mountain. The easier of the rainbow mountains to hike. The scenery was stunning, there were no crowds and the hike was very achievable.\n​I cannot say enough wonderful things about Carlos, William and Juan and the entire Peru Summit team. I was attracted to the organization based on their skills but also their mission of taking care of their people and helping the communities. I saw this in action by engaging with Sonia and Andean Colors but also in smaller ways like buying a special bread before our Palccoyo hike and distributing it amongst community members walking as we drove to our hiking spot. The community members were very appreciative.\n​I highly recommend using Peru Summit Adventures for your tours/excursions!	Liza Marchetti	5
