42c099fe-3dc6-49a5-b951-79a25d079f52	b1a92544-37a5-4337-89ce-8f2d26adeb4f	We booked a Sacred Valley day trip with Peru Summit Adventures and it was, without a doubt, the highlight of our entire time in Peru. From start to finish, every detail was taken care of and we left with memories we’ll cherish forever.\nOur tour guide Simon was absolutely world class. His knowledge of the Sacred Valley was impressive and his energy was infectious throughout the day. What truly set him apart was his genuine care for the people he was guiding - he went out of his way to facilitate a very special moment for my fiancé and me, something we will never forget. If you’re lucky enough to have Simon as your guide, you’re in for a treat.\nOur driver Juan was equally fantastic - professional, reliable, and a pleasure to be around. He made every transfer smooth and comfortable.\nWe came away having learned so much about the history and culture of the Sacred Valley, and we had an absolute blast doing it. If you’re visiting Peru, do yourself a favor and book with Peru Summit Adventures. You won’t regret it!	Thomas J	5
befa49d9-eace-410d-b2d3-7c6f1e293a1c	b1a92544-37a5-4337-89ce-8f2d26adeb4f	If you are planning to visit Cusco or any of the many amazing attractions in and around Cusco, including everything from Machu Picchu to Rainbow Mountain and beyond, I would HIGHLY RECOMMEND Peru Summit Adventures! They are incredible! I sent my wish list to Carlos and he turned it into a full detailed itinerary for me that was flawless! Our driver, Percy, picked us up at the airport in Cusco and took us to the hotel when we arrived late in the evening the first night. Then the next morning, Percy and our tour guide Simon picked us up at the hotel to take us to the Sacred Valley and had several amazing stops along the way including the Moray Ruins, Maras Salt Mines, the Ollantaytambo Fortress and more! They dropped us at the hotel in Ollantaytambo at the end of the first day and gave us a great restaurant recommendation for dinner. Day 2 we took the train to Aquas Calientes and then the bus to Machu Picchu where Simon guided us through with an awesome tour of the archeological site. We then tried to take the train back to Ollantaytambo but a cargo train had derailed and the trains were down the rest of the day. But Simon and Carlos helped us find a great hotel for the night there rather than waiting it out with hundreds of people in the train station and they also took care of getting our train tickets changed for the next morning. Day 3 after we took the train back with Simon to  Ollantaytambo, Percy was there waiting for us to take us to the Pisaq Archeological Ruins and the town of Pisaq where Simon guided us through the ruins and then down the mountain and into the town before they took us back to our hotel in Cusco for the night. Finally, the next morning, Percy came to take us to the airport for our return flight to Lima. Percy and Simon were awesome!!!! The entire experience was incredible and they took care of EVERYTHING for us each day with the logistics, tickets, transportation, tours, etc. Carlos recommended great hotel options for us as well which was the only thing we had to book ourselves. We opted for a private tour so it was just the two of us with the same driver and tour guide throughout the trip. And everywhere we went, so many people knew our tour guide Simon and stopper to say hello to him and he said hello to many people along the way as well. Worth every penny! Best travel experience with any tour company I’ve ver had and they handled so many details for our three days in the Cusco area! Thank you so much Carlos, Simon, and Percy and the entire Peru Summit Adventures team!	Jeff Butler	5
