b550004e-d3f1-42a5-8ad6-255223eaa603	d293aab0-5d8a-4a83-8d6b-13d24937110a	We did a 21 mile ride through sacred Valley. It was gorgeous! I was riding through ancient farmland, past fields of fluffy llamas, down by the river with black pigs wallowing in the mud, children on the mountain side with their llamas. We saw families working on a small plot of potatoes. Rode up high above the ruins Moray.   Got an amazing birds view there.\n\nRode through the tiny town and had a lunch included a delightful overlook. Appetizer, entrée, drink, dessert included .\n\nThe restaurant had a big green grass lawn and tasty food. Clean bathrooms with toilet paper and soap. Then we continued further in sacred Valley to the salt mine. We could see it from far above and then dropped all the way down to the salt mine and were able to walk around and get free salt and buy some salty chocolate.\n\nThere is some double track in beautiful country. A lot of single track. It definitely had some gnar and spice. Lots of downhill. Fast and exciting. For me this is the absolute best way to see sacred Valley… Rolling on two wheels!\n\nWe were visiting from Utah and mountain bike all the time.  we don’t get to see giant agave bushes and wallowing pigs and llamas and Peruvians in their traditional dress at home! SOOOO FUN.	erika wilde	5
