74628c04-87ad-4576-843c-7da3bbba76da	896bdc50-7ca9-4ceb-910a-26ebdfd213a5	Completing the 5-day Salkantay Trek with Salkantay Trekking was honestly one of the best experiences of my life. Every single day was unforgettable — from the snow-capped mountains and the incredible Salkantay Pass to the jungle landscapes and finally arriving at Machu Picchu. The entire trip was extremely well organized, with amazing food, beautiful accommodations, and breathtaking scenery at every step. Many reviews mention how seamless, beautiful, and life-changing this trek is, and I can completely understand why now.\n\nA special thank you to our guide Dorgan, who was absolutely wonderful throughout the whole journey. He was incredibly patient, kind, knowledgeable, and supportive — especially even when dealing with some challenging clients in the group. He always kept the energy positive, made everyone feel safe and motivated, and shared so much about the local culture, history, and nature along the way. You could really tell how much he cared about giving everyone the best possible experience.\n\nThe trek itself is challenging, but the reward is beyond worth it. The landscapes constantly change, the atmosphere within the group becomes so special, and reaching Machu Picchu after days of hiking makes the experience even more emotional and unforgettable. I would 100% recommend this adventure to anyone visiting Peru.	Anderson	5
890a8a47-4b56-4d4a-874e-ad6448b7e4b5	896bdc50-7ca9-4ceb-910a-26ebdfd213a5	Thanks to Uriel for such an incredible hiking experience, definitely a highlight of our South America travels. As a guide, Uriel was very knowledgeable, positive, enthusiastic, and managed our group well. He was also clear about what each day would entail and was just a lovely person! Our chefs (Jhojan and his dad) were incredible too, they prepared delicious and varied meals each day and catered well to dietry requirements. It was some of the best food we've eaten in Peru. The accommodation was very cool too - Mountain Sky View on day two was a real luxury after a tough day of hiking. Salkantay Trekking is great as they organise people into smaller, well matched groups and because of the attention to detail e.g. giving everyone hot water bottles on the first night as it was chilly. I would highly recommended to anybody considering the Salkantay Trek!	Fiona L	5
