9609b4f7-c903-41e4-9b47-fdf1df094935	896bdc50-7ca9-4ceb-910a-26ebdfd213a5	*One of the most memorable experiences of my time in Peru*\n\nI joined the 4‑day Choquequirao trek with Salkantay Trekking, guided by Marco, and it was truly outstanding. Marco is an exceptional guide – deeply knowledgeable, calm, funny, and incredibly attentive to everyone’s needs. His passion for the mountains, the culture, and the history added so much depth to the journey.\n\nThe organization of the entire trek was excellent. Everything ran smoothly, from transportation to camp setup. The equipment was high‑quality: sturdy tents, warm sleeping gear, comfortable mats, and reliable trekking poles. You can feel that the company invests in good materials to make the experience safe and enjoyable.\n\nA special highlight was the cook. The meals were far beyond what you would expect on a remote trek like this. Every dish was fresh, nourishing, and full of flavor. The ingredients were clearly chosen with care – lots of vegetables, fresh fruit, warm soups, and creative meals that kept us energized for long days of hiking. It felt like eating in a mountain restaurant rather than a campsite.\n\nThe mules and muleteers were also handled with great respect and professionalism. The animals were well cared for, well equipped, and treated gently. It gave me a lot of peace of mind to see how responsibly the team works with them.\n\nAnd of course, the landscape is simply breathtaking: dramatic canyons, cloud forests, endless mountain ridges, and finally the quiet, powerful presence of the Choquequirao ruins. Reaching this place almost alone, without crowds, felt magical.\n\nThis trek was one of the most meaningful experiences of my entire trip. I would choose Marco and the Salkantay Trekking team again without hesitation. Truly unforgettable.	Larissa R.	5
