d9d458f6-39ae-498c-86fd-194fc4f60071	a1a6f4f7-310d-4257-ad86-8788b19bf663	Christian approached us outside the entrance to the site and helped with our purchasing of the tickets (before we even agreed to hire him as a guide) which was a great help.\n\nAt this point he offered his services and on entering the site he gave us a choice of 3 different routes and prices.\n\nWe always want to do as much as possible so opted for the longest tour of 2hr 30 mins. ( we are mid 60s, reasonably fit, I have asthma)\n\nThe steps up to the ruins are easy to negotiate; if not tiring with the altitude but Christian stopped at different terraces and used these stops to fill us in on all the history.\n\nHis English is superb and you can tell he treats this with a passion which is always great to hear.\nWe learnt so much.\n\nHe took so many photos of us at various stops and even managed to make me look good (ish😁)\n\nAfter ascending the ruins we spent quite a while at the top and he pointed out another ruins behind the football pitch, (which we visited in the afternoon) .\n\nOn the steady decent he also stopped a few times.\n\nWe then visited the lower ruins with more photo stops and we finished off with the Llamas and Alpacas.\n\nWe can honestly say this was one of   ( if not the ) best descriptive tours we have ever had.\n\nWhen it came to payment we were a little short on Soles and Dollars but this was not a problem as his brother has a shop where we could pay by card.\n\nThis part is what really confirmed how great and trusting the Peruvian people are.\n\nThere was a festival going on that day and his brother was involved, meaning the shop was shut.\n\nChristian told us no problem and that we could arrange to meet him later on to pay!!!!\n\nWe exchanged phone numbers and returned later to settle up.\nWe did tip in soles cash.\n\nIf you are in doubt about who to use in Ollantaytambo look no further.\n\nThank you again Christian 👏👏👏	Simon Hallam	5
