81730e12-4243-417b-b97c-75a628c4ffb8	25c7afdd-29d5-448e-9285-6ac7e38d5a5e	I joined the 4-day Collpa de Guacamayos & Sandoval Lake tour with Andean Top Expeditions, and it was an unforgettable journey into the Amazon. The entire trip was very well coordinated, which allowed me to simply enjoy the experience without worrying about logistics.\n\nEach day brought something special: the macaw clay lick was truly breathtaking, with hundreds of macaws filling the sky in a burst of color and sound. At Sandoval Lake, we had the chance to see monkeys leaping through the trees, giant otters swimming close to our boat, and caimans resting along the shoreline — moments that felt straight out of a documentary.\n\nThe lodges were cozy and clean, offering a comfortable stay while still being surrounded by the jungle. The meals were delicious and plentiful, always fresh and full of flavor. Our guide was excellent, combining deep knowledge of the Amazon with a genuine passion for sharing it.\n\nOverall, the tour offered the perfect balance of adventure, wildlife encounters, and relaxation. I can confidently say that Andean Top Expeditions delivers a truly authentic Amazon experience that I would recommend to any traveler.\n\nI didn't take many photos, I just enjoyed the experience.	Bastian Muñoz	5
