ec373e2b-db2d-404f-9ea3-47eea75df58b	fc3e1849-3781-435d-8d31-20ca4740633a	Thank you Peru Private Tours for our trip to Rainbow Mountains! We had a 8:00 trip, and it was a great choice, guys! At some point we were alone at the view point! Our guide Nadia  took great care of us, explaining us about altitude, what to do, checking our conditions constantly (5000 meters is no joke!). Location for lunch - amazing, delicious food! The only flow of late departure tour is that the weather may worsen, but it the price for having all breathtaking mountains for yourself, just be prepared clothes-wise.\nPlace definitely worth visiting! Magnificent scenery!\n\nAlso we have guide for Machu Picchu from them, it was great also!	Natalia Kiuntieva	5
cfa16c47-092e-4dbe-8898-076a22a59acf	fc3e1849-3781-435d-8d31-20ca4740633a	What an amazing day. Very spontaneously we planned a full day tour to Palcoyo Mountain, the so called alternative rainbow mountain. Man, were we lucky. Everything was really professional from the initial contact to getting back to our hotel.\nWe were picked up in the morning at 7am, which is at least two hours later than most (or all) of the other tours start. The effects of this? Additional sleep and we bet the crowds. When we arrived at the place, most other tours already left or were about to leave, so the place felt almost private. Our driver Hugo and our guide Nayda did such a good job. They were always acting professionally and at the same time bringing in their amazing personality, knowledge and humor.\nWe experienced a wonderful day, including pick up at the hotel, snacks in the morning, a great time at the Palcoyo, including a part of the hike with llama and alpaca, a great lunch afterwards and a safe transfer back to the hotel. My full recommendation!!!	Jürgen Laux	5
