4d948989-df59-4030-b0a0-10aff84425d0	fc3e1849-3781-435d-8d31-20ca4740633a	I had an absolutely stellar time on the full day dyeing and weaving workshop with Peru Private Tours. Our guide, Naida, picked us up from our hotel in Cusco where we met up with one other family to drive to Calca for our workshop. We were greeted by several women from different communities in Peru where we all introduced ourselves (with translation done by our amazing guide, Naida). We then learned about different plants and minerals used for the dyeing process. We walked around area and located plants that were harvested and prepared by the group to use to dye our own wool. We had fresh fruit as a snack (they taught me how to peel and eat a passionfruit!) we also had a home cooked lunch that we shared with the women. We all got to weave our own piece (a choice between a bracelet or a bookmark) and we were each paired up with one of the women who helped us from start to finish. I honestly can’t say enough good things about this rich experience. Naida seemed genuinely happy to be sharing part of the culture with us, and she took TONS of photos and videos for everyone. The women were absolutely amazing (shout out to Ruth, Lucia, Marisol, and the others I sadly can’t remember the names of). I especially appreciated that it didn’t feel rushed or performative. We took our time and spent the whole day here. This was a highlight of our time in Peru and is different from the typical things everyone does. I can’t recommend this tour and company enough!	Jennifer Heaton	5
