f53c0ce9-0b5a-49b4-85bf-10d722599357	31e55367-47f8-4d74-bccb-ba3ce5a56224	I was thinking about sharing my experience at all, because I was afraid that maybe some future passangers would decide not to do a tour with this company based on our experience, and the last thing I want to make someones life bad.\nBut I will share it anyway....Im not assessing the rainforest and jungle, thats a 10/10 I am commenting the company and thr organization.\n\nMy communication with the company was not that satisfying, yes they did answer fast, but the infos were scarce and vague. I needed to ask 10x for the same thing, just to get an adequate answer.\nI has a feeling, that the owner really dislike me - for example my husband and I MUST pay in cash, case otherwise we cant participate, then they changed the exchange rate (we use Euros and not usd, so exchange rate to soles was changes based on the company's rate)...ok, but on thr debriefing everyone else paid with card (!!!). I mean we just felt stupid...\n\nWe didnt get the room that was on the photos, room for us was on the first floor with the bathroom in the ground floor - reaaaally uncomfortable to do this without electricity, whixh you dont have after 9 pm and when we went on early mornijg hike - we also did everything in a complete darkness. I dont expect 24/7h electricity in the jungle, I hope that we get the room that was advertised and on which we agreed upon. But that unfortunately didnt happen. Eventhough all other couples got the right lodges, we were told that those other ones (our lodges) are for couples only. (I mean also the moment when we felt stupid).\n\nOur tour guide Edwin is a very ambitious guide, he wanted us to see ALL. And we did , on the first day. No other group saw so much animals as we did...but at what cost? I didnt come to break my bokes RUNNING through muddy uneven terrain to see an animal. For me is thr experience just to be there. The first day was avsolutely exhausting and was not according to the plan we were out from 5 am until 9 pm with 30 min lunch break. Edwin is really fast, so he was always 50-100 m ahead, and just as we catch a glimpse of him he was going away again. On one hike 50% of the time he wasnt even on the horizon so we did it on our own. When we talked to him about it, he apologizes formally and did the same thing on the next hike.\nBecause it was absolutely exhausting for us to continue in that pace, we decided to shorten the tour from 4D/3N to 3 days and go back with another group.\n\nAll in all, the experience of being in the jungle and the rainforest is really great, maybe this company needs to fix some bugs within itself and then it would be perfect.	Anida Ademovic	3
