84f82e96-ec7f-49ee-bdb2-5af85ee48cbb	cmp1qfjis002eml2if99w8fgs	We did the full-day tour to the 7 Lakes of Ausangate with Peru Hike, and honestly, it was one of the most amazing experiences we’ve had in Peru. From the moment they picked us up at our hotel, everything was perfectly organized. The transportation was punctual, comfortable, and the staff was friendly and professional throughout the entire day.\n\nAfter a few hours on the road, we arrived at the starting point of the hike, where we were offered a warm and hearty breakfast—just what we needed to get ready for the adventure ahead. The scenery was already breathtaking at that point, with towering mountains and fresh air that fills you with energy.\n\nWe chose to do the route on horseback, and it was the best decision. The trail is long and at a high altitude, so riding allowed us to fully enjoy the views without getting exhausted. The horses were well cared for, and the local horsemen were kind, attentive, and always nearby to assist.\n\nThe lakes themselves are absolutely stunning. Each one has a different color—turquoise, green, deep blue—surrounded by snow-capped peaks, glaciers, rivers, and incredible high-Andean landscapes. It’s the kind of place that makes you stop in awe every few minutes just to take it all in.\n\nWe were guided throughout the day by Gilton, and we couldn’t have asked for a better guide. He was knowledgeable, kind, patient, and clearly passionate about the region. He shared with us local legends, history, insights about the Andean communities, wildlife, plants, and how the lakes change with the seasons. He was always making sure we felt good, safe, and were enjoying the journey.\n\nAt the end of the hike, we were served a delicious lunch, freshly made with local ingredients—perfect to refuel after the trek. We had some time to relax, take in the final views, and then returned to Cusco comfortably.\n\n✨ All in all, it was a magical and unforgettable day—beautiful landscapes, rich culture, amazing food, and a team that truly cares about giving you the best experience.\nI 100% recommend this tour with Peru Hike, and if you can, ask for Gilton as your guide. Thank you for such a special day!	Tin Polosr	5
b0cb2319-2208-4416-ad79-b04a7e887f62	cmp1qfjis002eml2if99w8fgs	I can’t find the words to fully describe how incredible the Ausangate & Rainbow Mountain 5-day trek was. Every single moment felt like a dream—majestic landscapes, peaceful trails, and a deep connection with nature that I had never felt before.\n\nFrom the very start, Perú Hike handled everything with total professionalism. I felt 100% safe, informed, and cared for. The logistics were perfectly organized, and the attention to detail was outstanding.\n\nEach day of the trek brought something new: stunning turquoise lakes, vast herds of alpacas, and the breathtaking presence of Ausangate Mountain (6,384 m / 20,945 ft). Sleeping in the Andes under a sky full of stars was an unforgettable experience. On day four, arriving at the vibrant Rainbow Mountain (Vinicunca) was simply magical—nothing compares to seeing it with your own eyes.\n\nA special thanks to our guide, Juan, who truly made the difference. He was knowledgeable, patient, and passionate about the mountains. He shared beautiful stories, always made sure we were okay, and created a strong sense of trust within the group. The meals were delicious and energizing, and the camping equipment was excellent.\n\nIf you’re considering doing this trek, don’t think twice. The scenery is out of this world, and with Perú Hike, you’re in the best possible hands. 100% recommended — trustworthy, professional, and deeply committed to an unforgettable experience.\n\nThank you, Perú Hike and Juan, for making one of my biggest dreams come true. 🙏✨	INGRID KORALIA TORRES QUISPE	5
