79bb4d06-cd99-4432-8c08-fc024cc1f207	68f9bcfa-79fc-44ea-99e3-991bf7548693	Trip during May before peak season.\n\nMelany and the team were extraordinary for our Machu Picchu and Sacred Valley trip. Upon arriving at Cusco airport, we utilized Taxi Datum service to transit to the hotel. Be aware that typical traffic in Cusco will turn into a 2hr+ trip. On our return back to Cusco, the hotel staff arranged a taxi for us at a better rate than Taxi Datum. Did not try to negotiate rates at the city center.\n\nThe hotel is a reasonable 15-20min walk to the train station for transit to Machu Picchu/Aguas Calientes. You are a <10min walk from city center plaza. And walking distance from the free granary hike. The nearby ruins are 70soles per person and well worth it.\n\nThe included breakfast is fairly reasonable and made to order. Let the hotel staff know when you want to have breakfast and they will have it ready for you at that time. The rooms are standard and average. Clean sheets and towels but not your luxury linens or pillows.\n\nPro tip: talk to the hotel staff about their special payment plan upon arrival. You will be paying less at a good discount than what your booking site states.\n\nOverall, great experience with this hotel and this central location. In one day, we were able to experience most of the Sacred Valley (Ollantaytambo ruins, granary, Moray, Moras Salt mine and Chincero) in less than 8hrs.	Ryan Chiem	5
