2d82dc2f-ff45-40b4-97ae-c77d00b38e5e	cmp1srwkp008vml2imhdh7c4d	Overall Impression: Sierra Sacred Valley is a stunning boutique property that strikes a perfect balance between high-end luxury and authentic Andean charm. With breathtaking mountain views and a resident group of 5 or 6 alpacas roaming the grounds, it offers a serene atmosphere that is ideal for decompression at either the start or end of a Peruvian itinerary.\nService & Dining\nThe service here is truly first-class—attentive without being intrusive. Due to the resort's remote and peaceful location, most meals are enjoyed at the on-site restaurant. Fortunately, the culinary program is exceptional; the food is flavorful, beautifully presented, and easily rivals top-tier urban establishments.\nThe Huchuy Qosqo Trek: A Hidden Gem\nOne of the standout features of this resort is their curated tour programming. I highly recommend the Huchuy Qosqo Trek. It is a roughly 10km hike along an original Inca route—a rare find that I didn't see offered elsewhere. For capable hikers, it is a special, immersive experience that feels far removed from the typical tourist trails.\nStrategic Logistics for Machu Picchu\nThe resort is excellently positioned for those planning a visit to Machu Picchu:\n• The Route: It is a quick and easy transfer to Ollantaytambo, where you can catch a direct train. This is a much more efficient strategy than traveling from Cusco, which results in a significantly longer and more exhausting day.\n• The Train Experience: I took the First Class service on the way up to enjoy the views and opted for the Prime train for the return. Since it’s dark on the way back anyway, the Prime service is a smart way to manage costs without sacrificing comfort.\nFinal Verdict\nWhile the property is a premium investment, the quality of the experience justifies the price tag. It is a world-class spot to relax and find your footing in the valley. Highly recommended.	Patrick L	5
fbbb60fa-da3d-4e75-b3b5-0e9d66cc22cb	cmp1srwkp008vml2imhdh7c4d	Nous avons passé 2 nuits à notre arrivée au Pérou et ce fut superbe. comme arrivée au Pérou on ne pouvait pas mieux rêver; tres belles prestations de l hotel, Louis le propriétaire est un livre ouvert sur la culture péruvienne, Bruno est aux petits soins pour les hotes, le chef cuisinier est excellent. les Alpagas dans le jardins sont affectueux et adorables. en plus l hotel est situé à une altitude moindre que Cusco ca permet de mieux s acclimater . le tout laisse des souvenirs impérissables. merci à eux	Dominique Bianchi	5
073670ae-b1dd-4986-b36f-8f5240822b42	cmp1srwkp008vml2imhdh7c4d	We loved our stay in Sierra! It is tucked away behind a quiet local town and we did not expect to see such a lovely place surrounded by mountains. Silvia the owner has been so accommodating - we landed late on our first night and even though they have closed their restaurant, Silvia made arrangements in advance so we could have hot noodle soup when we arrived. Her husband introduced the resident rescue alpacas which are super cute. The common area is so cozy and beautifully designed. Highly recommend!	Tinny Chan	5
