d1db7f74-a8a8-4a06-baf3-4e337983d72c	cmp1sspkw0090ml2iq1pvlef3	Visited Sacred Valley Peru April of 2026. Attended a retreat nearby  for a week but had the pleasure of discovering Inkasaire Boutique Lodge prior and post my retreat .\n\nInkasaire Boutique Lodge is unique and unforgettable offering spacious rooms, ample sitting areas to relax both inside and outside, jacuzzi, bonfires and star gazing. Sweet and tame Alpacas on premises to enjoy traditional pets: feeding, observing and mingling with, if you so desire.\n\nThe place is family owned and operated with future expansion to host group celebrations and then some. Beautiful views of multiple Apus (sacred mountains) to meditate or simply appreciate in peace. Family hosts an array of experiences from chef style meals catered at each individual’s request, site seeing archeological sites with guides, visiting near by towns and an opportunity to acclimate to altitude along with  traditional horticulture exploration if you so desire to learn and even educative astronomy sessions. All these and many more exciting amenities and excursions. Found this business to be affordable, reliable, and safe environment to explore Sacred Valley.\n\nWhen you contact Inkasaire Boutique Lodge, you will be welcomed and appreciated. They take the time to recommend additional experiences to your stay, such as: horseback riding, massage, ceremonies, hiking and more. They also offer shuttle service to and from airport.\n\nThey are located within a close- knit community that comes together with celebrations throughout the year. If you are lucky, you may experience one depending on time of year you visit.\n\nLook forward to returning and creating more abundant memories with my family and friends, as we felt at home during our stay at Inkasaire Boutique Lodge!!!	Paula Sandoval	5
