5e3162bb-679c-4e11-9b9c-778130be2383	cmp1sfh2w007qml2ihqly15xu	This small but historically significant archaeological site offers a unique perspective outside of the main Cusco ruins. Located deep in the humid Ceja de Selva (High Jungle), Huamanmarca served as a crucial Inca administrative and control center.\nIts primary function was to manage and store valuable tropical products (like coca, fruits, and feathers) traded from the Amazon basin. The architecture here uses lighter materials, typical of structures built in a humid, dense environment. It is a powerful reminder of the Inca Empire's expansive reach and sophisticated logistical planning across vastly different climates. A fascinating stop if you are traveling the alternative route!	Michal Rogozný	4
