0ffe3c94-1964-4f90-966a-b3dce9275dc1	cmp1thzmx00a8ml2i97ps6sa8	Antonio and Nicole are absolutely wonderful people. They alone make this place more than worth staying at. They could not have been kinder all the way from my booking process through my stay.\n\nThe main portion of my room was very clean and spacious; further, the bed was extremely comfortable. The bathroom is tight but manageable. Hot water and shower pressure were great.\n\nI was provided a fantastic breakfast which included eggs to order (I had an omelette), yogurt, granola, pineapple smoothie, and toast among other things. There was plenty of coffee and tea (including coca tea) provided.\n\nAs other reviews have mentioned, their place is away from the center of town which is quite noisy. Do keep in mind that Ayllu B&B boarders active farms. This B&B is an easy walk from the center of town or you can take a tuk-tuk for about 5 sols.\n\nOllantaytambo does not have five star hotels or really any typical hotels that I could discern; therefore, you need to stay in a place like this when lodging in this town. That being the case, why not stay in the best one which is here and receive the great hospitality from these exceptional hosts :-).\n\nHighly recommended!	Barrett	5
