3af00791-2dbb-4dd4-9b9f-fe4a2091a23d	cmp1thzmx00a8ml2i97ps6sa8	My friend and I stayed in two rooms at Ayllu B&B for two nights while hiking and acclimatizing in preparation for the classic Inca Trail hike to Machu Picchu.  We enjoyed our stay and would happily stay there again.  The small B&B is run by a friendly couple, Antonio and Nicole.  They were very accommodating and helpful arranging rides, sharing local information, and storing bags.  The rooms were simple but nice.  The beds were excellent, and I got great sleep there.  It was a quiet location while we were there – we liked being a little out of the noisier town area.  The shower was nice with good hot water supply.  There’s only cold water at the sink which seemed common in Peru.  Breakfast was simple but very good.  It’s a very nice place and a great value.	David Coggin	5
